WEBVTT

01:21.708 --> 01:22.909
Welcome home.

02:07.019 --> 02:10.455
Few men have had both
the courage and compassion

02:10.489 --> 02:12.892
possessed by our dear judge.

02:12.925 --> 02:16.428
Let us show the compassion
that he showed others

02:16.461 --> 02:19.297
by following the words
of our dear Lord

02:19.331 --> 02:22.034
from Matthew chapter 5.

02:22.068 --> 02:25.705
"You have heard it said that
you should love thy neighbor

02:25.738 --> 02:27.640
and hate thine enemy,

02:27.673 --> 02:31.343
but I say unto you,
'Love your enemy.'"

02:54.867 --> 02:56.769
They're crowding in.

02:56.803 --> 02:59.371
I need a drink, Abel.

02:59.404 --> 03:00.539
It's early.

03:02.975 --> 03:05.912
Mm, mm, mm.

03:05.945 --> 03:07.647
That was a beautiful service,
right?

03:07.680 --> 03:10.683
Yeah, Daddy would be proud.

03:13.618 --> 03:15.487
Oh, don't give me that look.

03:15.520 --> 03:17.360
Even God can see
the necessity of getting drunk

03:17.389 --> 03:19.759
on a day like today.

03:47.419 --> 03:48.788
Thank you, Walter.

03:48.821 --> 03:50.422
Good luck.

03:53.159 --> 03:55.795
Baby, there's a whole
lot of folks out there

03:55.828 --> 03:57.997
that want to pay their respects.

03:58.030 --> 03:59.732
Okay.

03:59.765 --> 04:01.033
Right.

04:01.067 --> 04:03.468
Let's get this over with.

04:07.640 --> 04:11.043
And her second husband
was a polo player.

04:11.077 --> 04:13.145
Doesn't it sound glamorous?

04:13.179 --> 04:15.748
Sounds to me
like she can't keep a man.

04:15.781 --> 04:17.783
- Divorced.
- Twice.

04:17.817 --> 04:20.052
- Are you busy later?
- And the other one,

04:20.086 --> 04:21.562
well they say
he wasn't much more than

04:21.586 --> 04:23.055
a playboy himself.

04:23.089 --> 04:24.924
Who would play around on her?

04:24.957 --> 04:27.459
Oh, my God, you act
as though you know her.

04:27.492 --> 04:29.461
You know she wouldn't
give you the time of day.

04:29.494 --> 04:31.130
What do you know
about fitting in?

04:31.163 --> 04:32.932
All the important men
were at the meatballs

04:32.965 --> 04:34.700
and you were at the dip.

04:34.734 --> 04:36.869
- It's all BS.
- It's communist talk.

04:36.903 --> 04:39.872
- Damn right.
- Them Yankees and unions.

04:39.906 --> 04:42.008
- Down here causing problems.
- Mhm.

04:42.041 --> 04:43.676
- Drink, sir?
- Thank you.

04:43.709 --> 04:45.678
Obliged.

04:45.711 --> 04:47.545
- Thank you.
- Very much.

04:49.749 --> 04:51.884
And it's that King and his boys.

04:51.918 --> 04:53.886
They're gonna send us all
to hell in a handbasket

04:53.920 --> 04:55.755
with the Civil Rights Bill.

04:55.788 --> 04:56.956
You gotta stop this nonsense.

04:56.989 --> 04:58.658
Now, hold on.

04:58.691 --> 05:00.893
We are nowhere near
hell in a handbasket.

05:00.927 --> 05:03.495
We are here to pay respects
to a good man,

05:03.528 --> 05:05.164
one of the best.

05:05.197 --> 05:06.999
Judge,

05:07.033 --> 05:09.735
your wisdom
will sorely be missed.

05:11.938 --> 05:13.571
- Safe landing.
- Here, here.

05:13.605 --> 05:15.573
Here, here.

05:23.249 --> 05:26.484
Smells like they put out
the meatballs.

05:26.518 --> 05:28.854
Come on, boys,
you can't miss this.

05:40.700 --> 05:42.534
Oh, my.

05:44.602 --> 05:46.639
Don't be shy, boys,
you better dig in

05:46.672 --> 05:48.016
'cause these puppies
are gonna go quick.

05:48.040 --> 05:49.651
Now, they got these
little toothpicks here,

05:49.675 --> 05:51.744
but I'm gonna grab
one of those plates.

06:04.190 --> 06:06.258
So sorry for your loss.

06:06.292 --> 06:08.194
Oh, thank you,
thank you so much.

06:08.227 --> 06:11.630
- Thank you for coming.
- Mhm.

06:11.664 --> 06:13.933
Maybe she'll come home
to run this place.

06:13.966 --> 06:16.202
That is not going to happen.

06:16.235 --> 06:17.737
- Thank you so much.
- I'm so sorry.

06:17.770 --> 06:20.572
- I know, it's so sad.
- Grace.

06:20.605 --> 06:22.241
Excuse me.

06:22.274 --> 06:23.685
I don't know how she does it,
but Mattie's cooking

06:23.709 --> 06:25.111
just gets better and better.

06:25.144 --> 06:27.545
Hi.

06:27.579 --> 06:29.815
Thank you for coming.

06:29.849 --> 06:32.918
- I'm gonna miss your father.
- Me too.

06:32.952 --> 06:35.221
Man, you are more beautiful
each time I see you.

06:35.254 --> 06:37.223
Mm.

06:37.256 --> 06:40.558
And you are always
a charming politician.

06:40.592 --> 06:43.029
Your father kept me up
on all your escapades.

06:43.062 --> 06:45.297
"Escapades," hm.

06:45.331 --> 06:47.199
Well, I hope
they weren't too boring.

06:47.233 --> 06:50.836
On the contrary,
I was living vicariously.

06:52.371 --> 06:54.082
Congressman, Sophia Spencer
needs to see you

06:54.106 --> 06:56.809
in the other room.

06:56.842 --> 06:59.945
Excuse me, my fan club awaits.

06:59.979 --> 07:01.981
- Call me if you need me.
- I will.

07:04.717 --> 07:06.152
Con...

07:07.853 --> 07:11.223
Miss... Mrs. Gordon?

07:11.257 --> 07:14.126
- Yes?
- I'm... I'm Bradford Lotts.

07:14.160 --> 07:17.763
I'll be the one at the bank
to handle your father's affairs.

07:17.797 --> 07:20.032
Clear... clear things up.

07:20.066 --> 07:23.235
- We will need to talk.
- Oh no, that's, um, fine.

07:23.269 --> 07:26.238
Just leave things as they are.

07:26.272 --> 07:28.040
- Well...
- And have you tried that dip?

07:28.074 --> 07:30.042
It's delicious. Excuse me.

07:32.912 --> 07:34.814
Snotty bitch.

07:34.847 --> 07:36.614
What did she say?

07:36.649 --> 07:39.085
Useless female,
that's what she is.

07:42.721 --> 07:44.090
Will you excuse me?

07:46.759 --> 07:48.828
Come on, Walter,
we're on the move.

07:48.861 --> 07:50.963
I'll catch you later.

07:50.996 --> 07:53.799
- You ain't get me nothing?
- You know I did.

07:53.833 --> 07:55.634
I wanna see this here.

07:57.670 --> 07:59.839
- No meatballs?
- You ingrate.

07:59.872 --> 08:01.783
I couldn't bring you meatballs,
the red barbecue sauce

08:01.807 --> 08:03.943
would stain my pocket.

08:03.976 --> 08:05.945
Best kitchen in 20 miles...
let's get rolling

08:05.978 --> 08:08.814
before another constituent
feels the need to chew my ass.

08:13.052 --> 08:14.420
All right, Walter.

08:22.394 --> 08:25.131
All right now.

08:25.164 --> 08:26.799
I look terrible in black.

08:26.832 --> 08:28.076
I mean, why wear black
to funerals?

08:28.100 --> 08:31.804
Why not red to celebrate?

08:31.837 --> 08:33.405
Daddy's life
should be celebrated.

08:33.439 --> 08:35.407
Sure should, baby, sure should.

08:35.441 --> 08:37.743
Now, get on out of this dress.

08:37.776 --> 08:39.678
You know what I heard them say?

08:39.712 --> 08:41.347
Narrow-minded little ninnies.

08:41.380 --> 08:43.382
- What'd they say?
- They said that I was

08:43.415 --> 08:45.251
a spoiled,

08:45.284 --> 08:48.387
middle-aged

08:48.420 --> 08:51.323
divorcÃ©e,

08:51.357 --> 08:55.027
and good for nothing.

08:55.060 --> 08:57.830
Ugh, oh, and useless.

08:57.863 --> 08:59.465
- That's what they said.
- Don't you mind

08:59.498 --> 09:02.134
what they sayin',
'cause you know who you are.

09:02.168 --> 09:04.336
No, maybe I don't.

09:04.370 --> 09:06.772
I know I've been...

09:06.805 --> 09:09.441
a good man's daughter,
and two not-so-good men's wife,

09:09.475 --> 09:13.379
but... I mean, otherwise,
am I useless?

09:13.412 --> 09:16.982
No, baby, don't fix your mind
thinking that.

09:17.016 --> 09:19.351
Our God has a plan.

09:19.385 --> 09:21.253
I wish I had your faith, Mattie.

09:21.287 --> 09:23.923
Well, it don't matter
if you do or you don't,

09:23.956 --> 09:25.491
He's still looking out for you.

09:25.524 --> 09:28.394
Ugh.

09:28.427 --> 09:30.496
- Thank you.
- You're welcome, precious.

10:24.917 --> 10:27.953
- Ooh, here we go.
- Where?

10:27.987 --> 10:29.788
Mm, mm, mm.

10:40.099 --> 10:42.234
- First, if you don't mind.
- Good morning.

10:42.268 --> 10:43.902
Hello.

10:45.971 --> 10:49.208
- Uh, Dad, the...
- Well, who are they...

10:49.241 --> 10:51.877
and what can they be
talking about?

10:51.910 --> 10:54.413
New York? Dick, come look.

10:54.446 --> 10:56.815
I'm watching The Secret Storm.

10:56.849 --> 10:59.485
Those TV airwaves
are gonna scramble your brain.

10:59.518 --> 11:02.488
Ugh, who cares?

11:02.521 --> 11:04.590
Gonna go around
with a scrambled brain?

11:04.623 --> 11:06.458
Well, sounds pretty good to me.

11:06.492 --> 11:08.527
And that's on your account.

11:08.560 --> 11:12.031
It's on account of a man like
you took an interest in me,

11:12.064 --> 11:13.866
and I wanna say thanks.

11:13.899 --> 11:15.410
Well, I'm glad things
are going well, Kate.

11:15.434 --> 11:16.969
Well, they seem to be,

11:17.002 --> 11:19.905
I report for
modeling assignments tomorrow.

11:19.938 --> 11:22.374
Ma'am, your meter has expired,

11:22.408 --> 11:26.178
and the new meter maid
is unforgiving.

11:29.581 --> 11:31.150
Thank you.

11:31.183 --> 11:32.484
Have a good day.

11:45.632 --> 11:47.533
Yes, ma'am, may I help you?

11:47.566 --> 11:50.402
I need to have a few words
with someone about my accounts.

11:50.436 --> 11:53.038
- Mr. Lotts.
- Mr. Lotts, yes.

11:56.008 --> 11:58.043
Can you tell him
that I'm waiting?

11:58.077 --> 12:00.546
Yes, ma'am, have a seat,
we'll be with you in a moment.

12:09.922 --> 12:12.324
I'm finished with this one,
if you want it.

12:12.358 --> 12:13.669
It's mostly about
Liz Taylor and her affair

12:13.693 --> 12:15.327
with that Welshman.

12:15.361 --> 12:17.596
Even a big movie star
has trouble with her men.

12:17.630 --> 12:19.898
Well, I guess you get
what you settle for.

12:19.932 --> 12:21.200
Yes, ma'am, I guess you do.

12:23.102 --> 12:24.346
Well, if we're gonna
talk about men,

12:24.370 --> 12:26.171
I should introduce myself.

12:26.205 --> 12:28.374
- Grace Gordon.
- I'm Ruth,

12:28.407 --> 12:30.609
and this is my girl, Angelina.

12:35.247 --> 12:37.383
Well, that's
a very pretty dress, Angelina.

12:37.416 --> 12:40.085
- Thanks.
- So fancy.

12:43.622 --> 12:45.190
God!

12:47.326 --> 12:50.129
I told you not to bother me
this morning, I am busy.

12:50.162 --> 12:52.164
Well, the office is filling up.

12:52.197 --> 12:53.633
One woman looks
like a real tart,

12:53.666 --> 12:55.401
and she's got a child with her.

12:55.434 --> 12:57.145
The way that child
is clutching a paper sack,

12:57.169 --> 12:58.937
I think it's full of money.

12:58.971 --> 13:00.673
And Mrs. Gordon is here.

13:02.374 --> 13:04.410
Oh!

13:04.443 --> 13:07.346
So, today is not going to be
a complete bore.

13:07.379 --> 13:10.115
She said she's here
to give you a few words.

13:10.149 --> 13:12.584
Oh, she is, is she?

13:12.618 --> 13:15.988
Well, I have a few words
for her as well.

13:20.660 --> 13:24.163
In, um... in 10 minutes,
I want you to come interrupt us.

13:25.397 --> 13:27.599
And is your dolly a good girl?

13:27.634 --> 13:30.502
- Mhm.
- Um, uh, Mrs. Gordon.

13:30.536 --> 13:32.538
- Please, please, come in.
- Well, these ladies

13:32.571 --> 13:34.674
- were before me.
- I... I insist, please.

13:34.707 --> 13:36.284
That's all right, ma'am,
we'll just sit here

13:36.308 --> 13:38.177
in the cool air.

13:38.210 --> 13:39.646
- Sure?
- Yeah.

13:39.679 --> 13:41.947
- It was very nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

13:45.050 --> 13:47.019
What are you doing here?

13:47.052 --> 13:49.321
I wanna put my money
in a safe place,

13:49.354 --> 13:51.032
and the paper says
you're giving out toasters

13:51.056 --> 13:52.701
- to new depositors.
- The bank doesn't take

13:52.725 --> 13:55.360
your kind of money.

13:55.394 --> 13:58.263
My money's green,
like everyone else's,

13:58.297 --> 14:01.166
and I earned it, the hard way,

14:01.200 --> 14:03.068
and who knows it
better than you?

14:06.639 --> 14:09.107
Come on, let's go.

14:11.410 --> 14:14.714
Please, have a... seat.

14:14.747 --> 14:17.549
Um, you know, I... I have called.

14:17.583 --> 14:20.185
I've, uh... I've left
several messages with...

14:20.219 --> 14:22.488
Yes, it seems like
there's been a breakdown,

14:22.521 --> 14:24.289
and had it not been for

14:24.323 --> 14:27.059
a stack of Mattie's famous
sweet potato pancakes,

14:27.092 --> 14:29.696
our water would've been
turned off.

14:29.729 --> 14:31.497
Well, uh, Mrs. Gordon,

14:31.530 --> 14:35.735
let's, uh... let's best see
how to describe this breakdown.

14:35.768 --> 14:38.805
The bank pays bills with money
from a customer's account...

14:38.838 --> 14:41.240
Yes, I know that.

14:41.273 --> 14:43.710
I have to go to lunch,
so if you could just

14:43.743 --> 14:47.579
deal with these quickly,
and move them forward.

14:47.613 --> 14:50.382
We don't really like
disturbances.

14:52.150 --> 14:54.086
No, no, most...

14:54.119 --> 14:56.355
most people do not like
disturbances,

14:56.388 --> 14:59.591
but, uh, you've got one now.

14:59.625 --> 15:03.128
You see, there is no money
in the account.

15:03.161 --> 15:05.330
I don't understand,
where was the money put?

15:05.364 --> 15:08.267
Well, your father transferred
a great deal of what he had

15:08.300 --> 15:09.802
to you over the years,

15:09.836 --> 15:11.470
and sold off land along the way

15:11.503 --> 15:14.674
to, uh, keep you up
in your adventures,

15:14.707 --> 15:16.743
oh, and... and marriages.

15:16.776 --> 15:18.778
Been two, right?

15:18.811 --> 15:22.180
So, the account
is dry as a bone.

15:22.214 --> 15:25.217
Now, the house
and what land is left are yours,

15:25.250 --> 15:27.452
but, uh,
the mortgage is overdue,

15:27.486 --> 15:30.155
and you'll have to sell.

15:30.188 --> 15:31.658
Sell?

15:31.691 --> 15:35.360
That house has been
in our family for generations.

15:35.394 --> 15:37.864
Times change, and besides,
farmland really isn't

15:37.897 --> 15:39.431
worth much these days.

15:39.464 --> 15:41.634
Mattie and Abel,
they've been on that land

15:41.668 --> 15:43.602
all their lives.

15:43.636 --> 15:45.437
Mattie's granddaughter's
with us, and she has

15:45.470 --> 15:47.339
no place to go.

15:47.372 --> 15:50.242
I have no place to go.

15:50.275 --> 15:52.311
No, I wouldn't dream of selling.

15:52.344 --> 15:56.582
Well, unless you've been
stashing money away somewhere.

15:56.615 --> 15:58.617
But, look,

15:58.651 --> 16:00.687
once you've paid off your debts,

16:00.720 --> 16:02.855
I mean,
if you don't live too long,

16:02.889 --> 16:05.157
you'll make do.

16:05.190 --> 16:07.694
Merner Courts would be
your best bet in town.

16:07.727 --> 16:10.228
Merner Courts?

16:10.262 --> 16:11.831
That's a retirement home.

16:13.900 --> 16:16.703
Mr. Lotts, you have a call,
someone important I think.

16:16.736 --> 16:19.639
Well, you've gotta do something,
extend the loan.

16:19.672 --> 16:23.275
Well, the, uh... the bank
only makes loans to men,

16:23.308 --> 16:26.311
and anyway, I really don't think
you'd be a good bet.

16:26.345 --> 16:28.614
I mean, you're 40, am I right?

16:28.648 --> 16:30.616
That is none of your business.

16:30.650 --> 16:32.652
Okay, well, near enough.

16:32.685 --> 16:35.253
Uh, no skills,

16:35.287 --> 16:38.725
no money, no man.

16:38.758 --> 16:40.860
I, uh... I think at this point
in you life, missy,

16:40.893 --> 16:42.527
you need to face facts:

16:42.561 --> 16:44.429
You are retired.

16:47.967 --> 16:49.534
How dare you?

17:20.298 --> 17:21.834
What's the matter, baby?

17:31.010 --> 17:32.712
We're broke.

17:32.745 --> 17:35.715
Tightening-our-belts broke,
or fending-off-the-wolves broke?

17:37.750 --> 17:40.485
- Wolves.
- Mm, mm, mm.

17:44.757 --> 17:47.459
And that scrawny little banker,
he said there's

17:47.492 --> 17:52.497
nothing I can do about it,
so there it is again, I'm...

17:52.531 --> 17:53.933
I'm useless.

17:53.966 --> 17:55.735
Now, you know you ain't useless.

17:55.768 --> 17:57.870
Well, what can she do?

17:57.904 --> 17:59.538
Well, just get another one.

17:59.571 --> 18:01.373
- Another what?
- Man!

18:01.406 --> 18:03.375
I don't want another one!

18:05.812 --> 18:07.312
That's our only option.

18:07.345 --> 18:08.715
Well, what about
the Congressman?

18:08.748 --> 18:10.950
Now, that is a good man,
and, baby, you remember

18:10.983 --> 18:12.919
you was flirtin' with him
when you was too young

18:12.952 --> 18:14.553
to be flirtin'.

18:14.586 --> 18:16.923
And he got
that government money.

18:16.956 --> 18:19.025
That kind don't ever run out.

18:19.058 --> 18:21.794
Ugh, yeah, and he's
a confirmed bachelor.

18:21.828 --> 18:25.631
Oh, God, I'll have
to brush upon my skills.

18:25.665 --> 18:28.533
Jubilee, go get
the judge's address book.

18:28.567 --> 18:30.803
So, you're what, you're gonna
choose one from a book?

18:33.773 --> 18:35.875
No, too old.

18:35.908 --> 18:37.777
- Or dead.
- Uh-uh.

18:37.810 --> 18:39.746
He spits when he speaks.

18:39.779 --> 18:41.814
- Mr. Parker, no.
- No.

18:43.482 --> 18:46.786
We both agree that 14,000 miles
of interstate highway

18:46.819 --> 18:48.654
is an incredible feat.

18:48.688 --> 18:50.622
But, with more funds,

18:50.656 --> 18:53.558
we could be
one nation under God,

18:53.592 --> 18:55.460
connected by asphalt.

18:55.494 --> 18:58.463
Yeah, well before you go patting
yourself on the back just yet,

18:58.497 --> 19:02.668
the Romans built
50,000 miles of road

19:02.702 --> 19:04.569
from sea to shining sea

19:04.603 --> 19:07.506
in 300 BC
without a single bulldozer.

19:07.539 --> 19:09.374
- Really?
- And no constituents

19:09.407 --> 19:11.911
calling to complain
about the cost,

19:11.944 --> 19:14.747
or the dust,
or the offensive billboards

19:14.781 --> 19:17.449
blocking their view
of their lovely hills.

19:19.384 --> 19:21.053
Emanuel Celler, again,

19:21.087 --> 19:25.524
and Alice Paul asking when
you might be available to talk.

19:25.557 --> 19:27.727
I know, the bill.

19:27.760 --> 19:30.863
Damn it, no rest for the weary.

19:30.897 --> 19:33.633
Thank you, Rachel.

19:33.666 --> 19:35.534
Listen, you want my support
for more funding

19:35.567 --> 19:37.703
- for this asphalt river?
- I do.

19:37.737 --> 19:39.872
No more graft.

19:39.906 --> 19:41.573
Clean this thing up,

19:41.606 --> 19:43.109
and give me more exits.

19:43.142 --> 19:45.011
And more fund...

19:46.979 --> 19:49.347
Tell the two of 'em
I'll get back to 'em

19:49.381 --> 19:52.051
just as soon as I'm able.

19:52.084 --> 19:54.720
You are a glutton
for punishment.

19:54.754 --> 19:57.355
I believe the word
is "masochist."

19:59.624 --> 20:01.627
Here you go,
here's your dress and drink.

20:01.661 --> 20:04.997
I made it strong
just the way you like.

20:05.031 --> 20:08.600
- Thank you.
- Mhm.

20:08.634 --> 20:10.703
- Mm.
- Do you still remember

20:10.736 --> 20:12.437
what to do on a date?

20:12.470 --> 20:14.573
Yeah, it's like riding a bike,

20:14.606 --> 20:16.676
and men are only interested
in one thing.

20:16.709 --> 20:18.610
Mm, snatch.

20:18.644 --> 20:21.113
No, I was referring
to their deeper need.

20:21.147 --> 20:24.549
- And what's that?
- Well, to talk about themselves,

20:24.583 --> 20:27.519
or just a sympathetic ear.

20:27.552 --> 20:29.521
I'm not about to be
a sympathetic ear

20:29.554 --> 20:31.724
- for no man.
- Oh, really?

20:31.757 --> 20:33.997
So, what are you gonna do,
you gonna make it on your own,

20:34.026 --> 20:36.095
- Miss Independent?
- Yes.

20:36.128 --> 20:39.165
There I was,
thinking you're a realist.

20:41.901 --> 20:43.468
Here.

20:44.804 --> 20:46.471
Why don't you try some,
try these on.

20:46.504 --> 20:47.807
Let me see you walk.

20:49.775 --> 20:51.552
- Where am I gonna wear these?
- I don't know,

20:51.576 --> 20:54.412
when you go
hootin' and hollerin'.

20:54.446 --> 20:57.783
- Oh no, I am not my mama.
- No, you got more sense.

20:57.817 --> 21:00.820
But you gotta go wild sometime,
you know, dance with abandon.

21:00.853 --> 21:02.889
That's how you dance,
with abandon?

21:02.922 --> 21:04.657
Mm-mm.

21:04.690 --> 21:06.726
I'm not allowed to be that free.

21:11.563 --> 21:13.766
You know, my first drink
that was at the Blue Goose,

21:13.799 --> 21:16.434
Abel waved me in.

21:16.468 --> 21:18.470
I learned two things
that summer:

21:18.503 --> 21:21.506
How to hold my liquor,
and how to dance

21:21.539 --> 21:24.877
like no one was watching.

21:24.911 --> 21:27.213
Oh, what a good time that was.

21:27.246 --> 21:29.614
Oh, I felt so free.

21:32.484 --> 21:35.487
"But now,
I cannot dance upon my toes.

21:35.520 --> 21:38.057
No man has instructed me."

21:38.090 --> 21:39.792
That's Emily Dickinson.

21:39.825 --> 21:41.593
Who's she?

21:41.627 --> 21:44.697
Just another woman
who had to dance backwards.

21:48.600 --> 21:51.170
Right, I'm about to

21:51.203 --> 21:53.839
sell myself
like a pound of meat.

21:55.741 --> 21:57.542
Hm?

21:57.575 --> 21:59.712
Yeah, I think I can
sell myself as prime.

22:01.247 --> 22:03.983
Spode, it's my favorite pattern.

22:04.016 --> 22:06.618
A man with taste, now that's
a great trait to have.

22:06.652 --> 22:08.788
I developed it
on my Italian travels.

22:08.821 --> 22:11.057
My mother lets me out
of her grip every summer.

22:11.090 --> 22:13.960
I go to Rome
for a month of utter bliss.

22:13.993 --> 22:16.195
Rome in the summer,
that's so romantic.

22:16.228 --> 22:19.799
Oh, I'm free to wander
the cafes and shops,

22:19.832 --> 22:22.802
meet all varieties
of interesting people.

22:24.602 --> 22:25.914
Now, a good boy
never kisses and tells,

22:25.938 --> 22:28.774
but, oh,

22:28.808 --> 22:30.676
some of the things I have done.

22:33.713 --> 22:36.282
But, mother's
tight purse strings

22:36.315 --> 22:38.985
pull me right back every time.

22:39.018 --> 22:41.020
She's never found a vice
she could embrace.

22:41.053 --> 22:42.965
The old penny pincher'll
probably have a grip on me

22:42.989 --> 22:45.891
my entire life.

22:45.925 --> 22:48.961
Uh, would you
excuse me a moment?

22:48.995 --> 22:51.230
Oh, Mattie, wrap it up,
one for him,

22:51.263 --> 22:53.032
and one for his mama.

22:53.065 --> 22:56.002
And... get the address book.

22:56.035 --> 22:57.636
All right, baby.

23:02.041 --> 23:04.542
They don't want us around here,
they keep doing their thing.

23:06.712 --> 23:08.156
So, y'all need to get
yourselves in the system

23:08.180 --> 23:10.750
and be registered
so y'all can vote.

23:13.819 --> 23:15.988
Listen to me.

23:17.089 --> 23:18.724
I'm right.

23:18.758 --> 23:20.826
I'm here for you.

23:20.860 --> 23:24.330
Jim Crow's biting me,
and he's biting you.

23:24.363 --> 23:26.699
Now, we should all
be equal under the law.

23:30.236 --> 23:32.038
Come on, y'all.

23:36.008 --> 23:37.877
This high-yellow fella
come down from the North

23:37.910 --> 23:40.112
to help us poor darkies out.

23:41.847 --> 23:43.615
I've come down to get you here

23:43.649 --> 23:46.752
to enlist you in the battle
of your equal rights.

23:46.786 --> 23:48.888
Equal rights?

23:48.921 --> 23:50.866
Abel, what you think about
this whole communist talk

23:50.890 --> 23:53.125
- he talkin' about?
- Just trying to figure out

23:53.159 --> 23:55.593
- what it all means.
- Yeah.

23:55.628 --> 23:57.930
Well, what it means,
Abel, is, uh,

23:57.963 --> 23:59.865
old Peanut here,

23:59.899 --> 24:02.001
he gonna get half
of what's yours,

24:02.034 --> 24:04.103
split down the middle,
share equal.

24:04.136 --> 24:05.905
Nah, nah, nah,
that's not what I mean.

24:05.938 --> 24:08.741
Yeah, Abel,
give me half your bill.

24:08.774 --> 24:10.776
He ain't got shit.

24:10.810 --> 24:13.646
- Lazy ass.
- Yeah, that's what it is, man.

24:13.679 --> 24:15.714
Well, he gonna take half of it.

24:15.748 --> 24:18.017
Not what I'm saying.

24:18.050 --> 24:20.086
See, old whitey here?

24:20.119 --> 24:21.687
He fought
the whole fuckin' world

24:21.720 --> 24:23.621
in World War II
defending this republic.

24:23.656 --> 24:25.133
- Yeah, he did.
- Old whitey's doing a good job

24:25.157 --> 24:27.126
- running things.
- Uh-huh.

24:27.159 --> 24:29.028
Streets are safe.

24:29.061 --> 24:31.397
- You got good-paying jobs.
- Mhm.

24:31.430 --> 24:33.299
And you men sleep
with your windows open.

24:33.332 --> 24:35.734
Now, what other animal lives
under that kind of protection,

24:35.768 --> 24:38.704
- huh?
- I know who you are.

24:38.737 --> 24:40.339
You drive the Congressman,

24:40.372 --> 24:42.384
and you'd like things to stay
exactly the way they are

24:42.408 --> 24:44.743
unless that man
tells you otherwise.

24:44.777 --> 24:46.378
Listen here, yellow boy,

24:46.412 --> 24:49.748
I don't kiss no one's ass,
I'm my own man.

24:49.782 --> 24:52.418
- That's right.
- The way I sees it,

24:52.451 --> 24:55.421
all the men here,
we're doing pretty goddamn fine.

24:55.454 --> 24:59.425
Yeah, you see, old whitey,
he got a plan.

24:59.458 --> 25:03.696
He building a highway
from the sea to shining sea.

25:03.729 --> 25:05.040
That shit's so big
they're gonna call it

25:05.064 --> 25:08.367
- a superhighway.
- Are you content?

25:08.400 --> 25:10.169
Are you content

25:10.202 --> 25:13.706
to pee by the side of that road?

25:13.739 --> 25:15.674
Sleep and eat

25:15.708 --> 25:19.845
where that white man
says your ass can?

25:19.879 --> 25:21.981
Jim Crow's gotta go.

25:22.014 --> 25:23.449
Y'all gotta register yourselves

25:23.482 --> 25:24.926
- and stand up.
- You're just itching to get

25:24.950 --> 25:26.285
your hand on that power stick,

25:26.318 --> 25:28.354
and you ain't got no plan,
yellow boy.

25:28.387 --> 25:30.289
You ain't got no plan.

25:30.322 --> 25:32.324
Mhm.

25:32.358 --> 25:34.693
Call me "yellow boy"
one more time...

25:34.727 --> 25:36.862
- And what?
- Hey!

25:36.896 --> 25:40.132
Hey, y'all gonna spend all night
fighting over about what?

25:40.166 --> 25:41.810
'Cause the only thing
gonna get settled tonight

25:41.834 --> 25:44.103
is who's gonna get
hot and sweaty, right?

25:45.871 --> 25:48.140
You.

25:48.174 --> 25:49.808
- You wanna dance?
- With all that

25:49.842 --> 25:51.443
white blood in him?

25:51.477 --> 25:53.212
He ain't gonna be able
to move much, baby.

25:54.947 --> 25:56.415
Well, you do gotta dance
in our shoes

25:56.448 --> 25:59.485
if you trying to...
trying to preach to us.

26:01.987 --> 26:03.822
Come on now,
I'll give you a dance.

26:05.424 --> 26:07.760
Hey, Abel,
you got some of that, uh...

26:07.793 --> 26:10.429
that good whiskey locked away?

26:10.462 --> 26:13.432
- Sure do.
- All right now.

26:13.465 --> 26:15.834
Break out something
for the boys.

26:15.868 --> 26:17.836
- On me.
- Two, come on, man, for me?

26:17.870 --> 26:20.005
- The lady, too.
- That's what I'm talkin' about.

26:20.039 --> 26:23.008
Now, y'all can't run
from the truth.

26:23.042 --> 26:25.878
You cannot run from the truth.

26:25.911 --> 26:28.314
- Okay.
- Jim Crow is alive and well.

26:28.347 --> 26:31.217
Please, please,
register yourself...

26:31.250 --> 26:33.352
- Okay.
- So you have equal rights.

26:33.385 --> 26:35.087
I hear you, man.

26:47.833 --> 26:49.835
Lord, Lord, Lord.

27:02.314 --> 27:05.784
You'll be all right,
you gonna be all right.

27:05.818 --> 27:08.320
You gonna be all right.

27:21.567 --> 27:24.003
Johnnie, Johnnie on the rocks.

28:39.345 --> 28:41.480
Ooh!

28:41.513 --> 28:44.083
You got back so soon.

28:44.116 --> 28:46.085
Yeah.

28:49.121 --> 28:52.925
That juke joint, like the one
my mama couldn't get enough of.

28:52.958 --> 28:55.094
Women throwing themselves
at men, hoping for something

28:55.127 --> 28:57.262
they ain't gonna get.

28:57.296 --> 28:59.998
Men arguing about
what they want and don't have.

29:00.032 --> 29:02.534
Mhm.

29:02.568 --> 29:04.671
Where do I fit in?

29:07.940 --> 29:09.375
Look up at that sky.

29:09.408 --> 29:12.679
Each one of them stars
shining from its own spot.

29:18.718 --> 29:21.186
He got a plan for us all.

29:31.163 --> 29:34.400
- Come on, now.
- Mommy, Mommy, Mommy!

29:34.433 --> 29:37.369
Mommy, Mommy, Mommy!

29:37.403 --> 29:38.705
- Mommy!
- Wow, are you

29:38.738 --> 29:41.106
feeding them kids good?

29:41.140 --> 29:42.608
Hm?

29:42.642 --> 29:44.552
- The scrawny little mutts.
- I put food on the table

29:44.576 --> 29:47.045
- the best I can.
- Mhm.

29:47.079 --> 29:48.390
You think those men
who gave me them children

29:48.414 --> 29:51.150
sending me money?

29:51.183 --> 29:53.118
I ain't got no steady work.

29:56.422 --> 29:58.390
What you got for me?

29:58.424 --> 30:00.192
Or am I just along for the ride?

30:37.196 --> 30:39.498
Walter.

30:39.531 --> 30:42.234
That boy last night.

30:42.267 --> 30:45.003
He said he's gonna
make us equal.

30:47.740 --> 30:50.075
Not you, baby.

30:50.108 --> 30:52.779
He wasn't talkin' about you.

31:20.506 --> 31:22.241
Hi, Andy.

31:22.274 --> 31:23.509
Hey, how are ya?

31:23.542 --> 31:25.177
Now, let's get this straight.

31:25.210 --> 31:27.680
There's a few more things
to take care of.

31:27.714 --> 31:30.750
So, all right,
have him looking sharp.

31:30.783 --> 31:33.720
Nothing sells better than
a well-dressed underdog.

31:33.753 --> 31:36.723
Trying to win a Pulitzer Prize,
aren't you?

31:36.756 --> 31:38.423
Camera ready,

31:38.457 --> 31:40.225
and no trouble.

31:40.259 --> 31:41.804
Don't you worry about that,
I'll have him singing Dixie

31:41.828 --> 31:46.298
and huggin' their mama,
if it gets us the front page.

31:46.331 --> 31:48.701
In Birmingham today,
police arrested

31:48.735 --> 31:51.436
Martin Luther King,
along with 58 other members

31:51.470 --> 31:54.072
of the Southern...

31:54.106 --> 31:55.583
Every time you turn around
something about some darkie

31:55.607 --> 31:57.242
causing trouble.

31:58.711 --> 32:00.345
NAACP.

32:00.379 --> 32:02.581
SNCC.

32:02.614 --> 32:06.151
Call themselves T-R-O-U-B-L-E,
make it clear.

32:06.184 --> 32:07.720
That is the same car.

32:07.754 --> 32:11.189
I'm tellin' ya, something
is getting ready to go down.

32:11.223 --> 32:12.567
George, ain't nothing
going down around here

32:12.591 --> 32:14.426
except your IQ.

32:14.459 --> 32:17.162
Oh, look at you, getting into
the Cutty Sark already

32:17.195 --> 32:19.598
and The Secret Storm,
haven't even started yet.

32:23.368 --> 32:27.272
Now, tell me about this
fascinating job you have.

32:27.306 --> 32:29.776
Ford automobile's a good value.

32:29.809 --> 32:31.243
Ford don't make anything cheap.

32:31.276 --> 32:33.512
Top of the line,
a Thunderbird V8.

32:33.545 --> 32:35.280
Well, that one's been
a big best seller

32:35.314 --> 32:36.683
for me this year.

32:36.716 --> 32:40.152
Can I get a top-off in here?

32:40.185 --> 32:41.888
Well, let's get to it.

32:41.921 --> 32:45.792
As a rich widow in town,
I know what this all about.

32:45.825 --> 32:47.760
This place is
expensive to keep up.

32:47.794 --> 32:49.528
Needs work.

32:49.561 --> 32:51.196
You need money.

32:51.229 --> 32:54.901
Of course, my dealership
prints it,

32:54.934 --> 32:58.503
long as Ford makes cars
like the Ford Galaxy.

32:58.537 --> 33:00.505
Nothing cheap there.

33:00.539 --> 33:03.609
It's got
a 390-cubic-inch engine.

33:03.643 --> 33:05.577
When that thing roars up,
it's like...

33:08.815 --> 33:10.415
Oh, my Lord, come on.

33:13.385 --> 33:15.554
Come on now,
spit it out, spit it out.

33:20.192 --> 33:22.795
Oh, Lord.

33:22.829 --> 33:25.464
Um, no dessert.

33:31.904 --> 33:34.406
It says, um, that you buy things

33:34.439 --> 33:36.441
that are useful and good.

33:36.475 --> 33:39.177
- That's right, I do.
- Well.

33:41.648 --> 33:43.515
Well.

33:45.317 --> 33:48.420
Say, uh, what does
this little one do?

33:48.453 --> 33:50.923
That's a pickle fork.

33:50.957 --> 33:54.192
It's 1800s,
my great-grandmother's.

33:54.226 --> 33:56.663
Huh! Teresa,
take a look at this.

33:56.696 --> 33:59.331
It's a fork just for a pickle.

34:01.868 --> 34:04.469
Oh, my goodness, a pickle fork.

34:04.503 --> 34:06.739
- Huh.
- And many a fine dinner

34:06.773 --> 34:08.908
it has seen, I'm sure.

34:08.941 --> 34:11.911
Unfortunately, fine dining items
just don't sell anymore.

34:11.944 --> 34:13.913
It's all been replaced
with the TV dinner.

34:13.946 --> 34:15.791
Before you know it, we won't
even be talking to each other.

34:15.815 --> 34:18.450
We'll just be lost
in our appliances.

34:18.483 --> 34:20.385
Amen.

34:20.419 --> 34:22.755
I hope it doesn't come to that.

34:22.789 --> 34:24.556
Gotta go, it's good
to meet you, ma'am.

34:24.589 --> 34:25.925
Good to meet you, too.

34:25.958 --> 34:27.359
- Bye, y'all.
- All right.

34:27.392 --> 34:28.728
Bye.

34:28.761 --> 34:30.930
Ma'am...

34:30.963 --> 34:33.733
I do give cash for diamonds.

34:37.737 --> 34:40.673
The only thing that
good-for-nothing paid for.

34:44.043 --> 34:45.978
That's beautiful,
let's have a look.

34:48.781 --> 34:50.482
Ah, yeah.

34:50.515 --> 34:51.784
Well,

34:51.818 --> 34:55.487
there is
a pretty significant flaw.

34:55.520 --> 34:57.456
How much?

35:01.560 --> 35:03.930
Are you talking to 'em, Walter?

35:03.963 --> 35:05.665
You tellin' 'em all that
pie-in-the-sky,

35:05.698 --> 35:08.500
everybody's-equal poppycrap
is just that?

35:10.302 --> 35:12.270
And things are nice as they are.

35:14.941 --> 35:16.575
I'm talkin' to 'em, boss,
but everybody

35:16.608 --> 35:19.045
don't listen to me, you know?

35:19.078 --> 35:21.346
They say
there's always two sides.

35:21.379 --> 35:23.281
Not always two right sides.

35:26.085 --> 35:27.854
Look out there.

35:33.391 --> 35:35.795
God did bless America.

35:35.828 --> 35:37.930
He really did.

35:47.707 --> 35:49.008
How do I look?

35:51.543 --> 35:53.079
Hm.

35:53.112 --> 35:54.881
Hm, what?

35:54.914 --> 35:57.449
A man ain't gonna buy the cow
when he can drink the milk

35:57.482 --> 35:59.417
- for free.
- I'm just letting him know

35:59.451 --> 36:00.953
that the cow's
still worth milkin'.

36:00.987 --> 36:02.688
Just...

36:02.722 --> 36:04.623
Mm, mm, mm.

36:11.563 --> 36:12.899
Now.

36:16.102 --> 36:20.472
Mm, could do with
a little bit more punch.

36:20.505 --> 36:23.843
Well, bit of valerian,

36:23.876 --> 36:25.945
little pinch of passionflower.

36:25.978 --> 36:29.048
I got it set, right?

36:29.081 --> 36:30.817
Before we use any more
of what we got left,

36:30.850 --> 36:32.685
we better make sure
this is what we want.

36:32.718 --> 36:35.520
Well, Lord, more spice
ain't gonna do no harm.

36:45.932 --> 36:48.701
It looks like we the only ones
at this dinner party.

36:57.609 --> 37:00.445
You come get me out, you hear me
making promises I can't keep.

37:00.478 --> 37:03.448
- Oh, I know the drill.
- How do I look?

37:03.481 --> 37:05.718
Like a man with no self control.

37:16.428 --> 37:18.664
Ladies, ladies,
what is that smell?

37:18.698 --> 37:21.033
Ooh, we're cooking all kinds
of wonderful things for you,

37:21.067 --> 37:23.135
- Congressman.
- Don't be wasting

37:23.169 --> 37:24.904
your fine herbs on me.

37:24.937 --> 37:26.939
I'm already under your spell.

37:26.973 --> 37:28.573
How is she, Mattie?

37:28.607 --> 37:30.676
- Has it been rough?
- She gettin' right along.

37:30.710 --> 37:32.477
Mhm.

37:32.510 --> 37:35.580
Oh, your magic herbs give you
an unfair advantage.

37:35.614 --> 37:37.192
Well, if I'd known
you were gonna be this easy,

37:37.216 --> 37:39.719
I wouldn't have opened
Abel's home brew.

37:39.752 --> 37:42.822
I am this easy, so be gentle.

37:42.855 --> 37:45.523
Look at you,
beautiful as always.

37:45.557 --> 37:48.861
Such a flatterer,
and it isn't even voting time.

37:48.895 --> 37:51.797
That's how you know I mean it.

37:51.831 --> 37:53.574
- How have you been?
- Oh, I don't even wanna think

37:53.598 --> 37:55.968
about that,
but you are the escape.

37:56.002 --> 37:58.204
The delicious escape.

37:58.237 --> 38:01.841
Well, let's, uh, go outside,
and pour ourselves a drink,

38:01.874 --> 38:04.710
and let's talk about
nothing important

38:04.744 --> 38:06.913
- all night long.
- Yes, ma'am.

38:08.814 --> 38:11.951
Jubilee, you take good care
of Walter tonight.

38:11.984 --> 38:14.519
Why I gotta take care of him?

38:14.552 --> 38:16.088
Because I said so.

38:18.556 --> 38:20.159
Thank you kindly, ma'am.

38:20.192 --> 38:21.694
Yes, sir.

38:23.763 --> 38:26.899
Why don't you sit down
and have you something to eat?

38:26.933 --> 38:29.702
How y'all doin', Miss Mattie,
with no man in the house?

38:29.735 --> 38:31.804
Uh, we doin' all right.

38:31.837 --> 38:33.940
How y'all doin'
up there in Washington?

38:33.973 --> 38:36.642
Well, a lot of talking,
but mostly same old grumbling.

38:38.811 --> 38:40.179
Now, who this here, Miss Mattie?

38:40.212 --> 38:42.949
You know her,
that's my grandbaby,

38:42.982 --> 38:44.750
Miss Jubilee Moody.

38:44.784 --> 38:47.920
Well, your grandbaby
sure grown up fast.

38:47.954 --> 38:49.822
I'm not the one up for sale.

38:49.855 --> 38:52.258
You sure?

38:52.291 --> 38:54.459
She's spicy, I like that.

38:56.662 --> 38:58.931
Mhm.

38:58.965 --> 39:01.233
God damn, it tastes so good.

39:12.244 --> 39:13.980
Oh,

39:14.013 --> 39:16.248
even the air out here
smells sweet.

39:20.820 --> 39:22.154
To you, Grace.

39:24.323 --> 39:25.958
To this place.

39:25.992 --> 39:27.693
To this night.

39:27.727 --> 39:28.995
To us.

39:32.164 --> 39:34.266
Mm.

39:34.300 --> 39:35.968
Mm,

39:36.002 --> 39:38.771
my mama used to make
muscadine wine.

39:38.804 --> 39:40.773
And me, an official of the law.

39:40.806 --> 39:42.017
Well, you aren't
gonna turn me in, are you,

39:42.041 --> 39:44.276
- Congressman?
- No, ma'am.

39:44.310 --> 39:46.645
Uh,

39:46.679 --> 39:47.919
you mind if I just help myself?

39:51.616 --> 39:53.551
Muscadine wine.

39:53.585 --> 39:55.321
That's America's grape,

39:55.354 --> 39:57.723
and you know,
every great civilization

39:57.757 --> 40:00.693
needs its own wine.

40:00.726 --> 40:02.237
Miss Mattie, I'm proud
how you're teaching

40:02.261 --> 40:04.663
your grandbaby
how to treat a man.

40:04.697 --> 40:06.198
Woo!

40:06.232 --> 40:08.167
She got some work to do,
though, huh?

40:14.606 --> 40:16.175
Quit studying me.

40:16.208 --> 40:18.878
Ah, you don't want me
to study, huh?

40:18.911 --> 40:20.913
Tell me,

40:20.946 --> 40:22.614
what you want old Walter to do?

40:22.648 --> 40:25.151
Nothing, you only here
'cause you driving the man.

40:25.184 --> 40:27.552
Ouch, come on, girl.

40:32.858 --> 40:34.894
He's eating out of her hand.

40:34.927 --> 40:36.629
I mean, he is actually eating

40:36.662 --> 40:39.632
right out of her hand.

40:39.665 --> 40:42.201
I bet he was droolin'
when he saw this fruit tart.

40:42.234 --> 40:44.103
Big old smile on his face.

40:44.136 --> 40:46.705
Big old stupid grin.

40:46.739 --> 40:50.242
Now, this here is
near the best I ever had.

40:50.276 --> 40:51.710
Near the best?

40:53.813 --> 40:56.148
Well, I'm saving
the category of best

40:56.182 --> 40:58.084
till I taste to know the rest.

40:58.117 --> 41:00.386
Look here,
do you come with this deal?

41:00.419 --> 41:02.655
'Cause we sure could
use the help around here.

41:02.688 --> 41:04.757
That roof leaks, for starts.

41:04.790 --> 41:06.792
Only thing is,

41:06.826 --> 41:08.994
you don't look like
you work much labor.

41:09.028 --> 41:12.098
Miss Mattie, y'all trying
to cut a deal with my man?

41:12.131 --> 41:13.642
Something you need to know
about him, sweet pea,

41:13.666 --> 41:15.000
he a politician.

41:15.034 --> 41:17.837
Now, he can be bought,
but he can't be had.

41:17.870 --> 41:19.905
Lifetime bachelor.

41:19.939 --> 41:22.341
Wanna bet we can't win him?

41:22.374 --> 41:25.311
You got something
worth wagering?

41:25.344 --> 41:27.279
No?

41:27.313 --> 41:29.782
How about a dance then

41:29.815 --> 41:31.884
at the Blue Goose?

41:33.919 --> 41:36.422
What's the matter,
you can dance, can't ya?

41:36.455 --> 41:38.791
Only thing is, I don't think
you'd ever find out.

41:38.824 --> 41:41.127
- You sure?
- Those wide loads of yours

41:41.160 --> 41:42.995
don't look none too graceful.

41:43.028 --> 41:45.164
Well, they know how to get
out of the way of long feet

41:45.197 --> 41:46.765
trying to stomp on 'em.

41:49.034 --> 41:51.170
So, we on?

41:51.203 --> 41:54.740
A dance for me if I get through,
and if, uh...

41:54.773 --> 41:56.909
if you win, well,

41:56.942 --> 42:00.112
I guess you got
your dedicated slave,

42:00.146 --> 42:03.149
and that roof up there
gonna get fixed.

42:03.182 --> 42:05.951
Oh yeah.

42:05.985 --> 42:08.053
- Shake.
- Yes, ma'am...

42:14.293 --> 42:16.228
What you got there, girl?

42:21.333 --> 42:23.002
Cubans.

42:24.737 --> 42:27.273
I suppose after all that trouble
with the Bay of Pigs,

42:27.306 --> 42:30.009
- I should've thrown them out.
- You're right.

42:30.042 --> 42:33.078
Can't let politics stand
in the way of a good cigar.

42:33.112 --> 42:34.980
Excuse me, Miss Gordon.

42:35.014 --> 42:37.116
It's been so nice
around here that

42:37.149 --> 42:39.051
time just done run away with us.

42:39.084 --> 42:40.853
Congressman,
you told me to remind you

42:40.886 --> 42:42.797
about the business you got
at the Capitol in the morning.

42:42.821 --> 42:44.957
- Not yet, Walter.
- Excuse me.

42:46.458 --> 42:48.003
You had too much to drink,
you're starting

42:48.027 --> 42:50.763
to make promises you can't keep.

42:50.796 --> 42:52.898
I suggest we get away
while we can.

42:52.932 --> 42:54.833
- Trust me.
- Yeah.

42:56.302 --> 42:58.103
My apologies, Grace.

42:58.137 --> 43:00.472
Seems the specter
of tomorrow has

43:00.506 --> 43:03.375
abrupted our festivities.

43:03.409 --> 43:06.779
Will I be invited back soon?

43:06.812 --> 43:08.180
I'll check my calendar.

43:10.182 --> 43:13.185
I am holding my breath,
so please,

43:13.219 --> 43:15.187
- don't wait too long.
- Come on now, Congressman.

43:15.221 --> 43:17.189
- All right, I got it, I got it.
- Thank you.

43:17.223 --> 43:18.757
Well, all right.

43:31.937 --> 43:34.273
Ah, that is some good stuff.

43:34.306 --> 43:36.075
You got that right.

43:36.108 --> 43:38.410
That girl Jubilee
ripe for the picking.

43:38.444 --> 43:40.446
There will be
none of that, Walter.

43:40.479 --> 43:42.057
I don't want you
muddying up these waters

43:42.081 --> 43:44.883
with your obsessive desire
to mark your spot.

43:44.917 --> 43:47.353
This gonna be my spot.

43:47.386 --> 43:49.021
I might just throw in the towel.

43:49.054 --> 43:53.359
Retire, let those fine wenches
take care of me.

43:53.392 --> 43:54.860
Retire, you?

43:56.562 --> 43:58.330
That's the wine talkin', boss.

43:58.364 --> 44:01.433
No, I've had an entire lifetime

44:01.467 --> 44:04.570
of managing the world order.

44:04.603 --> 44:07.406
I wanna just

44:07.439 --> 44:09.541
float.

44:09.575 --> 44:11.243
Ain't gonna be
no floatin' around here.

44:11.277 --> 44:14.546
That Jubilee already taking bets
about me doing some roof.

44:14.580 --> 44:15.581
Know what I'm saying?

44:15.614 --> 44:17.249
There's gonna be no retiring.

44:53.285 --> 44:57.389
"All good men

44:57.423 --> 45:00.526
should come to the aid

45:00.559 --> 45:02.161
of their country."

45:04.963 --> 45:08.000
- Oh, God, what's the time?
- 7:30.

45:08.033 --> 45:11.136
- What... what you doing?
- You know, out of 60 ads,

45:11.170 --> 45:13.539
there's only eight for women,
and only one of those

45:13.572 --> 45:15.474
barely applies to me.

45:15.507 --> 45:17.076
What they payin', babe?

45:17.109 --> 45:19.646
Pay dependent on skills.

45:19.679 --> 45:21.947
The plant person
at Sea Graves Trucking...

45:45.070 --> 45:46.639
Hello.

45:46.673 --> 45:48.273
I'm Grace Gordon,
I'm here for the job

45:48.307 --> 45:49.908
of girl Friday.

45:49.942 --> 45:52.945
Here, fill this out.

45:52.978 --> 45:55.080
Over there with them others.

45:55.114 --> 45:56.114
Do you have a pencil?

45:59.451 --> 46:01.253
Thank you.

46:07.626 --> 46:09.428
Yeah, you better get out here.

46:09.461 --> 46:11.964
My office is fillin' up.

46:11.997 --> 46:13.499
Y'all here for the job?

46:13.532 --> 46:15.668
Yes.

46:15.702 --> 46:18.937
My husband's been out of work
for a few months now.

46:18.971 --> 46:22.408
We got two kids, and...

46:22.441 --> 46:25.678
we're staying with
his sister's family.

46:25.712 --> 46:28.480
I gotta get out of there
before they drive me crazy.

46:30.449 --> 46:32.951
My mother can't work no more.

46:32.985 --> 46:34.553
I'm supportin' us both.

46:36.355 --> 46:37.657
What you here for?

46:37.690 --> 46:39.992
Extra spending money?

46:40.025 --> 46:41.493
No.

46:41.527 --> 46:43.562
I'm also here for my family.

46:46.999 --> 46:49.968
Okay, what we got here?

46:50.002 --> 46:52.304
All right, uh, May Jones.

46:52.337 --> 46:54.540
Yes, sir, I'm May Jones.

46:56.375 --> 46:57.744
Can you type, honey?

46:57.777 --> 46:59.411
Yes, sir,

46:59.445 --> 47:01.146
a little.

47:01.180 --> 47:02.682
But, if you hire me,

47:02.715 --> 47:06.084
I bet I can do just about
anything you ask me to do.

47:08.020 --> 47:10.989
Ooh, that's the kind of answer
I like to hear.

47:11.023 --> 47:12.692
All right, uh,

47:12.725 --> 47:14.993
Nell Brown.

47:17.095 --> 47:18.698
Mm.

47:18.731 --> 47:22.301
Uh, see here you got experience.

47:22.334 --> 47:24.203
Type 100 words a minute?

47:24.236 --> 47:27.072
Yes, sir, I take shorthand, sir,

47:27.105 --> 47:29.308
and if you need, sir,
do your accountant work,

47:29.341 --> 47:30.576
too, sir.

47:30.609 --> 47:32.444
Hm.

47:35.514 --> 47:37.616
And you.

47:41.353 --> 47:43.288
Grace Gordon.

47:43.322 --> 47:45.591
- Yes, sir, that's right.
- You graduated

47:45.624 --> 47:47.392
from Hollins College

47:47.426 --> 47:51.129
with a degree in...
19th century poetry?

47:51.163 --> 47:53.766
- Yes, and I also have...
- Married?

47:53.800 --> 47:56.168
- Divorced.
- Hm.

47:56.201 --> 47:59.338
And I also type,
not as quickly as these ladies,

47:59.371 --> 48:02.374
but if I'm given the job,
I can certainly help this place

48:02.407 --> 48:04.343
look less like a...

48:04.376 --> 48:07.546
like a truck stop.

48:07.579 --> 48:10.048
As the adage goes,

48:10.082 --> 48:11.550
"A man is judged
by his appearance,"

48:11.583 --> 48:14.620
and I can certainly
help with that.

48:14.654 --> 48:16.723
Hm, divorced?

48:18.490 --> 48:21.527
Okay, let's have
a quick turn around, girls.

48:23.128 --> 48:24.664
All right,
lift skirts a little bit.

48:30.335 --> 48:31.771
Are we applying
for the chorus line

48:31.804 --> 48:34.106
or a secretarial job?

48:34.139 --> 48:36.542
Everything must be appealing,
didn't ya say?

48:38.577 --> 48:40.345
Let's go in the back,
honey, come on,

48:40.379 --> 48:42.139
let's go know each other
a little bit better.

48:44.182 --> 48:45.617
Oh!

48:48.186 --> 48:50.455
Well.

48:50.489 --> 48:52.190
I guess the interview is over.

48:52.224 --> 48:55.527
Yeah, I think he got
all he needed to know.

48:55.561 --> 48:57.095
I'm too ugly,

48:57.129 --> 49:01.166
and you're too bossy.

49:08.373 --> 49:10.242
This is The Secret Storm,

49:10.275 --> 49:11.811
brought to you by Dristan.

49:13.746 --> 49:16.649
The measure of our leadership
is in rebuilt inventories,

49:16.683 --> 49:19.484
increased production
all along the line.

49:19.518 --> 49:21.386
The measure of our leadership

49:21.420 --> 49:23.322
is the measure of the future.

49:27.426 --> 49:29.494
When'd you get this?

49:29.528 --> 49:31.664
Brought it in a few days ago.

49:31.698 --> 49:33.565
Mrs. Grace Gordon

49:33.599 --> 49:35.133
came in proud as you please.

49:35.167 --> 49:36.736
That belonged
to her grandmother.

49:36.769 --> 49:38.671
- Hm.
- Can you just imagine

49:38.705 --> 49:40.572
all those society evenings?

49:40.606 --> 49:42.809
- That's fancy.
- Well, did you know

49:42.842 --> 49:45.277
she lived in Paris, France,
for a while?

49:45.310 --> 49:46.679
Hm.

49:46.713 --> 49:49.581
She must be hard up for money.

49:49.615 --> 49:51.550
It's the same car,

49:51.583 --> 49:52.861
the one with
the New York plates.

49:52.885 --> 49:54.787
I'm tellin' ya,
something is goin' on.

49:54.821 --> 49:56.555
Sure, George.

49:56.588 --> 49:58.499
Probably Time magazine
come all the way down here

49:58.523 --> 50:00.760
to report on paint drying.

50:00.793 --> 50:03.863
- Where?
- Right there, the black sedan.

50:03.896 --> 50:05.376
- That one right there?
- Right there.

50:06.966 --> 50:08.901
- Hello.
- Oh!

50:08.935 --> 50:10.937
Well, look at you,
fresh as a daisy.

50:10.970 --> 50:12.705
We were just talkin'
about your valuables.

50:12.739 --> 50:15.607
Oh, was anything sold?

50:15.642 --> 50:18.276
Well, no, not yet.

50:18.310 --> 50:20.245
All right, well.

50:20.278 --> 50:21.914
Whoops, better get back to work.

50:21.948 --> 50:23.850
I am in need
of a little more money

50:23.883 --> 50:26.753
for something special
I'm working on,

50:26.786 --> 50:29.689
and I wonder how much
I could get for these.

50:29.722 --> 50:32.224
I mean,
it's costume jewelry, but,

50:32.257 --> 50:34.661
- anything?
- Well...

50:36.528 --> 50:37.797
these are very beautiful.

50:39.398 --> 50:42.735
Wish I had someone
to give 'em to.

50:42.769 --> 50:44.278
You know, Dick, you should
buy something like this

50:44.302 --> 50:45.905
for your wife.

50:45.938 --> 50:48.908
- Do something nice.
- Why?

50:48.941 --> 50:52.344
She ain't give me
nothing but a hard time.

50:52.377 --> 50:55.280
Well, that's no way to be.

50:55.313 --> 50:58.718
I can loan you $35 to $40
for the lot.

51:02.021 --> 51:05.792
You know, I was thinkin'
about you the other day.

51:05.825 --> 51:07.794
Here's, uh...

51:11.831 --> 51:14.466
Have a look at this here paper.

51:14.499 --> 51:16.501
It says, uh,

51:16.535 --> 51:18.403
"Make the world
a beautiful place,

51:18.437 --> 51:20.238
and make money doing it.

51:20.272 --> 51:21.841
Avon is coming to your area,

51:21.874 --> 51:26.012
and there's
new territory for sale."

51:26.045 --> 51:28.380
Maybe this is for you.

51:32.517 --> 51:35.253
Door-to-door sales?

51:36.923 --> 51:40.727
Honey, 60-day loans
roll around real fast.

51:45.363 --> 51:48.835
Yeah, and I may have managed
to stage a narrow escape.

51:48.868 --> 51:50.703
We'll see.

51:53.572 --> 51:56.008
- Right there.
- Well, I didn't count on that.

51:56.042 --> 51:59.311
Well, I'm guessing you will.

51:59.344 --> 52:02.614
I can do this here.

52:02.648 --> 52:04.349
What do you think of that?

52:04.382 --> 52:07.053
- Uh-huh.
- Oh, Congressman,

52:07.086 --> 52:10.723
I can see you're up to
your same old tricks.

52:10.757 --> 52:13.458
I might have one or two
left in the bag.

52:16.796 --> 52:19.598
- I can say...
- Oh, well, just say it.

52:21.399 --> 52:24.070
I win.

52:24.103 --> 52:26.571
Congratulations, Earl.

52:26.605 --> 52:27.916
Yeah, I think this is
the first time

52:27.940 --> 52:29.709
in two or three years
you beat me, well,

52:29.742 --> 52:31.576
well done, well done, my friend.

52:31.610 --> 52:33.445
All right, Tiny.

52:33.478 --> 52:35.648
That is my last four bits.

52:35.681 --> 52:36.949
Robbery.

52:36.983 --> 52:38.426
You know, you should be
ashamed of yourself

52:38.450 --> 52:40.352
treating your congressman
like this.

52:40.385 --> 52:41.854
I gotta go, boys,
I got work to do,

52:41.888 --> 52:43.890
but I wanted to give you
a little something here.

52:43.923 --> 52:45.390
All right.

52:45.423 --> 52:46.692
Here it is.

52:48.895 --> 52:51.363
Tell 'em to have
a look at this here.

52:51.396 --> 52:52.832
Oh yeah.

52:52.865 --> 52:55.868
A little gift for you, boys.

52:55.902 --> 52:58.738
Niggas got bones
in their nose in Africa.

53:00.539 --> 53:02.440
God bless America, huh?

53:02.474 --> 53:04.744
- Congratulations.
- Bones in our noses

53:04.777 --> 53:07.345
and wings on our backs.

53:10.582 --> 53:14.053
Now, boys, aren't y'all tired
of being excluded?

53:14.086 --> 53:16.421
Huh? We gotta
register ourselves.

53:16.454 --> 53:17.256
We gotta be in the system.

53:17.290 --> 53:19.524
We gotta be...
we gotta be counted.

53:27.800 --> 53:29.635
Get out of here.

53:29.669 --> 53:30.468
You all right?

53:30.502 --> 53:32.370
- Watch your head.
- That's crazy.

53:32.404 --> 53:34.606
Don't come around here.

53:34.640 --> 53:38.144
