won't sing âª

53:38.177 --> 53:41.981
âª Mama's gonna buy you
a diamond ring âª

54:10.643 --> 54:11.643
Avon.

54:15.014 --> 54:17.049
Hello? Avon.

54:29.195 --> 54:30.763
Hello? Avon.

54:38.037 --> 54:39.772
Avon calling.

54:39.805 --> 54:42.540
Here to make your day
more beautiful.

54:42.574 --> 54:44.844
My man don't allow
nobody on his property.

54:44.877 --> 54:47.747
I'm not here for him.

54:47.780 --> 54:50.116
I'm here for you
and I got products.

54:50.149 --> 54:52.852
Ma'am, I ain't got no money.

54:59.225 --> 55:01.626
You're a beekeeper?

55:01.661 --> 55:02.962
Yes, ma'am.

55:02.995 --> 55:04.730
Well, that's beautiful.

55:04.764 --> 55:06.198
I always wanted
to be a beekeeper.

55:09.601 --> 55:11.203
You don't want no run-in
with him.

55:11.237 --> 55:12.238
Please go.

55:12.271 --> 55:14.106
Who is that on my property?

55:14.140 --> 55:15.607
Um...

55:15.641 --> 55:17.143
Well, I'm here to see your wife.

55:17.176 --> 55:21.647
Um, see if she's interested
in some products.

55:21.681 --> 55:22.801
Well, she ain't go no money.

55:23.816 --> 55:24.951
So get.

55:26.919 --> 55:28.821
Go on now. Get on out of here.

55:36.629 --> 55:38.230
A girl should always have
mad money.

55:41.634 --> 55:43.002
Every lady always needs honey.

55:44.270 --> 55:45.537
I said get, bitch.

56:06.225 --> 56:07.525
- Woo!
- I got her!

56:07.559 --> 56:09.261
I got her, I got her!

56:09.295 --> 56:11.263
What? Help!

56:11.297 --> 56:12.732
What? Help!

56:12.765 --> 56:13.866
Good God Almighty, boys.

56:13.899 --> 56:15.634
What have y'all done?

56:15.668 --> 56:17.003
You from the truants' office?

56:17.036 --> 56:18.180
I told them boys
to get to school,

56:18.204 --> 56:19.805
but they don't mind me.

56:19.839 --> 56:21.040
No, I'm Avon.

56:21.073 --> 56:23.541
I'm here to make
your day more beautiful.

56:23.575 --> 56:24.653
Reading, writing, and 'rithmetic

56:24.677 --> 56:25.978
don't mean shit if all they do

56:26.012 --> 56:27.313
is produce heathens.

56:27.346 --> 56:28.447
Manners.

56:28.481 --> 56:30.850
That's what they need
to be teachin' in schools.

56:30.883 --> 56:32.952
These heathens
are your next citizens.

56:32.985 --> 56:34.754
Yes, you have a point.

56:34.787 --> 56:36.822
I'm not from
the truants' office.

56:36.856 --> 56:39.158
Can you get your boy off of me?

56:39.191 --> 56:41.559
Leave that woman alone
and act right for once.

56:41.593 --> 56:42.962
Not until you call uncle.

56:42.995 --> 56:45.031
Let go of whoever
you've got this instant,

56:45.064 --> 56:47.166
Bobby Jo, you hear me?

56:48.300 --> 56:49.300
You hurt?

56:50.302 --> 56:51.871
A little.

56:51.904 --> 56:54.707
It's you, from the bank.

56:54.740 --> 56:56.742
Miss Grace Gordon.

56:56.776 --> 56:59.178
I'm Ruth, remember?

56:59.211 --> 57:00.179
Yes.

57:00.212 --> 57:02.181
If you don't mind me askin',

57:02.214 --> 57:04.250
what in the name
of Sam Hill are you doin' here

57:04.283 --> 57:05.284
on this side of town?

57:05.317 --> 57:07.253
Avon, here to make your day
more beautiful.

57:07.286 --> 57:10.356
But I'm... I'm not doing
a very good job.

57:10.389 --> 57:12.590
Avon?

57:12.624 --> 57:14.927
To this neighborhood?

57:14.960 --> 57:18.164
Well, you landed
in the right place now.

57:18.197 --> 57:20.699
Come on,
I'll get you cleaned up.

57:20.733 --> 57:22.034
Thank you.

57:24.637 --> 57:25.871
Golly.

57:25.905 --> 57:27.373
Now you don't mind, do you, uh,

57:27.406 --> 57:30.810
comin' in, I mean,
and gettin' somethin' to drink?

57:30.843 --> 57:32.845
Do you have bourbon?

57:32.878 --> 57:34.246
Why, yes, ma'am, we sure do.

57:34.280 --> 57:36.082
Then I'd be delighted.

57:39.752 --> 57:41.687
Girls, we got a caller.

57:41.720 --> 57:43.689
Things gonna make you
even more beautiful.

57:43.722 --> 57:45.124
Come look.

57:48.427 --> 57:50.696
Miss Effie, we got Avon.

57:50.729 --> 57:51.729
Huh?

57:53.365 --> 57:55.067
Girls.

57:55.101 --> 57:56.769
Avon.

57:56.802 --> 57:58.237
Straighten up.

58:04.677 --> 58:07.046
- Here you go, Miss Grace.
- Thank you.

58:07.079 --> 58:08.156
You got a room
full of ready customers,

58:08.180 --> 58:10.015
don't she, girls?

58:10.049 --> 58:12.685
Everyone, this is my friend,
Miss Grace Gordon.

58:12.718 --> 58:14.820
And she's here
with some nice things.

58:16.222 --> 58:18.958
- Well, um...
- That's right, baby doll.

58:18.991 --> 58:21.327
This is a hootchie-cootchie
titty house.

58:21.360 --> 58:22.795
Queenie, stop it.

58:22.828 --> 58:25.798
Miss Grace, money don't know
no prejudice,

58:25.831 --> 58:28.367
and we're workin' girls
that got money.

58:30.703 --> 58:32.037
Well, that's right.

58:35.207 --> 58:36.842
Well, all right, come on.

58:36.876 --> 58:38.644
Right this way.

58:42.982 --> 58:44.884
I have some very nice items.

58:44.917 --> 58:46.452
Honey, we ain't lookin'
for nice.

58:46.485 --> 58:48.120
Come on.

58:48.154 --> 58:50.923
Look at this.

58:50.956 --> 58:53.025
Scheherazade's Arabian Nights.

58:53.058 --> 58:54.860
Now don't that sound exotic?

58:54.894 --> 58:56.729
Shoot, sounds hot to me.

58:56.762 --> 58:57.897
And expensive.

58:57.930 --> 58:58.998
You're cheap, Queenie.

58:59.031 --> 59:01.901
Bet you got the first dollar
you ever got laid for.

59:01.934 --> 59:04.370
Don't you worry
'bout what I got.

59:04.403 --> 59:07.339
You got anything to cover this
in that bag of tricks?

59:07.373 --> 59:08.373
Here.

59:09.775 --> 59:11.911
Did someone hit you?

59:11.944 --> 59:12.954
Some people think hurtin' you

59:12.978 --> 59:15.247
comes with the price
of the ride.

59:15.281 --> 59:16.415
It's okay.

59:16.448 --> 59:18.484
Miss Effie keeps a gun.

59:18.517 --> 59:19.952
Scheherazade.

59:19.985 --> 59:21.787
Who was she to get a perfume
named after her?

59:24.390 --> 59:26.859
It's Scheherazade.

59:26.892 --> 59:29.828
Now, let me tell you about her.

59:29.862 --> 59:33.732
See, in a far away land,
there was a king.

59:33.766 --> 59:37.069
And each night, he chose a wife.

59:37.102 --> 59:39.438
And every day, he beheaded her.

59:39.471 --> 59:40.506
You know why?

59:40.539 --> 59:42.975
'Cause he didn't want her
to be unfaithful.

59:43.008 --> 59:45.144
But when Scheherazade
was chosen,

59:45.177 --> 59:47.046
she outsmarted him.

59:47.079 --> 59:50.182
She spun a tale
that was so intriguin'

59:50.216 --> 59:51.984
that the king kept her alive

59:52.017 --> 59:55.321
for 1,001 nights
just to hear more.

59:55.354 --> 59:59.225
And then she became his queen.

59:59.258 --> 1:00:02.161
This day started off
just like any other regular day

1:00:02.194 --> 1:00:04.463
and then you dropped in
and made it magic.

1:00:04.496 --> 1:00:07.032
No, you've been the one
doin' all the sellin'.

1:00:07.066 --> 1:00:08.200
You'd be good at sales.

1:00:08.234 --> 1:00:11.937
No, no one's gonna hire
an uneducated hillbilly like me.

1:00:11.971 --> 1:00:14.039
Nah, I gotta play to my assets.

1:00:14.073 --> 1:00:16.342
Plus, I got a little girl
to take care of.

1:00:16.375 --> 1:00:18.177
I'm gonna make sure
she's educated.

1:00:18.210 --> 1:00:20.813
She's gonna be
a fine lady like you.

1:00:20.846 --> 1:00:22.381
All right, girls.

1:00:22.414 --> 1:00:24.416
Tea party's over.

1:00:24.450 --> 1:00:25.884
Ruth, Bay Bay,

1:00:25.918 --> 1:00:28.120
you're on the window tonight.

1:00:28.153 --> 1:00:31.924
It's a two-drink minimum,
on top no matter.

1:00:31.957 --> 1:00:33.392
Come on, get a move on.

1:00:36.962 --> 1:00:38.964
I hope our paths cross again.

1:00:38.998 --> 1:00:42.401
I won't speak up or nothin',
just smile,

1:00:42.434 --> 1:00:44.436
if you won't mind it.

1:00:44.470 --> 1:00:45.838
Of course.

1:00:45.871 --> 1:00:47.439
Honey, you got your order ready.

1:00:47.473 --> 1:00:48.540
You need to pack it up.

1:00:48.574 --> 1:00:50.576
We got business.

1:00:50.609 --> 1:00:51.609
Yeah.

1:00:52.611 --> 1:00:53.611
All right.

1:00:56.181 --> 1:00:58.350
What did y'all learn
at school today?

1:00:58.384 --> 1:00:59.918
Wow.

1:01:03.188 --> 1:01:06.959
A, B, C,

1:01:06.992 --> 1:01:09.995
D, E, F, G.

1:01:12.498 --> 1:01:13.332
$6.70,

1:01:13.365 --> 1:01:18.337
and then two Skin So Softs
at $5.78.

1:01:20.205 --> 1:01:23.242
$20.03.

1:01:23.275 --> 1:01:24.977
Easy money.

1:01:26.445 --> 1:01:29.381
Sorry, did you just do that
in your head?

1:01:29.415 --> 1:01:31.617
Got a head for figures, I guess.

1:01:31.651 --> 1:01:33.085
Yes, you have.

1:01:34.153 --> 1:01:35.120
And for sellin'.

1:01:35.154 --> 1:01:37.289
You should do somethin'.

1:01:37.323 --> 1:01:40.426
Somethin' better than this.

1:01:40.459 --> 1:01:42.227
Better?

1:01:44.463 --> 1:01:46.065
I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to be rude.

1:01:46.098 --> 1:01:48.267
It's just that... you could.

1:01:48.300 --> 1:01:52.104
You're... useful.

1:01:52.137 --> 1:01:53.972
This ain't no regular life
for you,

1:01:54.006 --> 1:01:58.577
but I was born
on the wrong side of the tracks.

1:01:58.610 --> 1:02:01.180
Ain't got no education
to speak of.

1:02:02.481 --> 1:02:04.516
But I'm a saver.

1:02:07.353 --> 1:02:09.656
Baby, you're gonna miss
the start of your show.

1:02:09.689 --> 1:02:12.024
- Okay.
- Go on, get your study books.

1:02:15.494 --> 1:02:17.296
- Bye.
- Bye.

1:02:22.167 --> 1:02:23.602
Well?

1:02:23.636 --> 1:02:25.270
How do I look?

1:02:25.304 --> 1:02:26.505
I look all right?

1:02:27.606 --> 1:02:28.675
Yeah.

1:02:38.117 --> 1:02:39.184
All right.

1:02:44.623 --> 1:02:46.392
For your future.

1:03:57.596 --> 1:03:59.998
Which one of these
you want to use tonight?

1:04:00.032 --> 1:04:02.601
Which one makes me look thinner?

1:04:02.635 --> 1:04:05.638
You ask a lot of these jackets,
Congressman.

1:04:05.672 --> 1:04:09.241
The art of flattery
will only assist you, Walter.

1:04:09.274 --> 1:04:10.509
You gonna stay the night?

1:04:10.542 --> 1:04:12.444
Up to the lady, of course.

1:04:12.478 --> 1:04:16.381
I do believe I have won my way
into her good graces.

1:04:16.415 --> 1:04:18.250
Congressman,
don't get all caught up.

1:04:18.283 --> 1:04:19.527
This woman is used
to nothing but high living.

1:04:19.551 --> 1:04:21.320
There's a lot of work
to do over there.

1:04:21.353 --> 1:04:23.355
Walter, I've been
playing this game

1:04:23.388 --> 1:04:26.158
since before you were a gleam
in your father's prick.

1:04:29.628 --> 1:04:31.196
No tie.

1:04:31.230 --> 1:04:32.699
Yes, sir.

1:04:48.815 --> 1:04:50.750
Mattie?

1:04:50.783 --> 1:04:51.784
Jubilee?

1:04:51.818 --> 1:04:53.686
We in here.

1:04:53.720 --> 1:04:55.521
All right, what's goin' on?

1:04:55.554 --> 1:04:57.489
The man done turned us off.

1:04:57.523 --> 1:05:00.459
He said they're a power company
not a charity business.

1:05:00.492 --> 1:05:02.394
Oh my God, what else can happen?

1:05:02.427 --> 1:05:05.264
Congressman called,
said he was ridin' into town

1:05:05.297 --> 1:05:08.200
and said we sure would be
a good sight to see

1:05:08.233 --> 1:05:09.334
if we wasn't doin' nothin'.

1:05:09.368 --> 1:05:10.402
With no electricity?

1:05:10.435 --> 1:05:12.504
Please do not tell me
that you invited him over.

1:05:12.538 --> 1:05:15.274
We've got to close
this deal tonight, baby.

1:05:15.307 --> 1:05:16.709
We in the dark.

1:05:16.743 --> 1:05:18.544
After the day I've had.

1:05:20.847 --> 1:05:22.614
How am I gonna pull that off?

1:05:27.586 --> 1:05:29.121
I'm glad to be goin' some place

1:05:29.154 --> 1:05:31.323
where there's not a care
in the world.

1:05:31.356 --> 1:05:32.825
- Yes, sir.
- And one of God's

1:05:32.859 --> 1:05:34.694
sweetest creatures
is gonna be treatin' me

1:05:34.727 --> 1:05:36.663
like I'm all that matters.

1:05:38.898 --> 1:05:41.533
Oh, Lord.

1:05:41.567 --> 1:05:43.135
What's goin' on?

1:05:43.168 --> 1:05:44.445
They sent one of them
rabble-rousers down here

1:05:44.469 --> 1:05:45.504
to stir things up.

1:05:45.537 --> 1:05:47.640
- Rabble-rouser?
- Yes, sir.

1:05:47.674 --> 1:05:50.151
Is that one of King's men or one
of those crazies from Chicago?

1:05:50.175 --> 1:05:53.111
One of King's men,
and a commie reporter too.

1:05:53.145 --> 1:05:55.113
Dammit. Streets are safe.

1:05:55.147 --> 1:05:56.615
Plenty of jobs.

1:05:56.649 --> 1:05:58.651
I'd say we've created
a kind of utopia.

1:05:58.685 --> 1:06:00.452
I wouldn't go that far.

1:06:01.654 --> 1:06:04.156
What did you say, Walter?

1:06:04.189 --> 1:06:06.191
Look at you, hm?

1:06:07.426 --> 1:06:08.627
Driving a Cadillac,

1:06:08.661 --> 1:06:10.495
getting all the snatch
you can handle.

1:06:10.529 --> 1:06:12.699
Hm? Back seat.

1:06:13.933 --> 1:06:16.335
You've had your fair share
of the pie in your day too.

1:06:16.368 --> 1:06:17.502
My day?

1:06:18.537 --> 1:06:20.138
This is still my day.

1:06:22.341 --> 1:06:25.444
My forefathers
wrote the Magna Carta

1:06:25.477 --> 1:06:27.847
and the Constitution
and the Boy Scout manual,

1:06:27.880 --> 1:06:29.816
three of the finest documents
ever written.

1:06:29.849 --> 1:06:32.417
And I'm still writin'
damn good law.

1:06:32.451 --> 1:06:34.687
Only thing
missing today is gratitude.

1:06:36.288 --> 1:06:38.457
Congressman, they just sayin'

1:06:38.490 --> 1:06:40.559
why can't a negro man
eat where he wants?

1:06:41.728 --> 1:06:44.363
Drink from the same fountain,
piss in the same pot?

1:06:45.798 --> 1:06:48.233
What's that all about, huh?

1:06:48.266 --> 1:06:51.938
Hell, Walter, let's just get
to where there's no trouble

1:06:51.971 --> 1:06:54.373
and no talk of change.

1:07:07.452 --> 1:07:09.354
Hm, hm, hm.

1:07:09.388 --> 1:07:10.522
Now what's this all about?

1:07:10.555 --> 1:07:12.424
What the hell?

1:07:21.834 --> 1:07:23.502
Y'all blown a fuse?

1:07:23.535 --> 1:07:25.404
Welcome!

1:07:25.437 --> 1:07:27.439
Well, what have we here?

1:07:27.472 --> 1:07:29.207
Scheherazade awaits.

1:07:29.241 --> 1:07:30.342
Follow me.

1:07:30.375 --> 1:07:32.377
Boss, be careful,
this looks like a trap.

1:07:33.512 --> 1:07:34.881
Lead the way, my sweet.

1:07:34.914 --> 1:07:36.381
Mm.

1:07:36.415 --> 1:07:37.850
Lead me away.

1:07:45.590 --> 1:07:47.727
Jubilee, Jubilee.

1:07:47.760 --> 1:07:48.828
Shut up.

1:07:56.636 --> 1:07:58.537
Grace.

1:07:58.570 --> 1:08:00.572
My Grace.

1:08:00.605 --> 1:08:02.975
What do you have on your mind?

1:08:03.009 --> 1:08:05.011
And will I live up
to the challenge?

1:08:07.412 --> 1:08:09.581
Well, I think
you'll manage just fine.

1:08:10.983 --> 1:08:13.418
Come curl up under.

1:08:13.452 --> 1:08:14.921
Let's enjoy the world.

1:08:15.955 --> 1:08:17.724
Sounds like a perfect plan.

1:08:26.966 --> 1:08:28.835
They say we're movin'
a thousand miles an hour

1:08:28.868 --> 1:08:30.870
through space.

1:08:30.903 --> 1:08:33.840
Yet down here it feels like
we sittin' still.

1:08:33.873 --> 1:08:34.941
Mm-hm.

1:08:36.374 --> 1:08:37.509
Yeah.

1:08:39.377 --> 1:08:42.447
This is all just an illusion,
really, isn't it?

1:08:42.481 --> 1:08:43.959
See, when I was young,
I used to see those lights

1:08:43.983 --> 1:08:45.017
in the distance.

1:08:45.051 --> 1:08:47.352
They'd sparkle like diamonds
and I thought...

1:08:49.621 --> 1:08:52.457
I was curious
to see what they were.

1:08:52.491 --> 1:08:55.061
After all of your travels,
you finally found that

1:08:55.094 --> 1:08:56.863
there's no place like home.

1:08:58.597 --> 1:08:59.732
Mm.

1:09:03.970 --> 1:09:04.970
Come on.

1:09:05.972 --> 1:09:06.972
What?

1:09:08.406 --> 1:09:10.442
Let's swim in the moonlight.

1:09:14.013 --> 1:09:15.782
Come on.

1:09:15.815 --> 1:09:17.817
I double-dare you.

1:09:17.850 --> 1:09:19.351
Beautiful.

1:09:20.619 --> 1:09:21.921
Oh, God.

1:09:24.891 --> 1:09:26.324
Oh my God.

1:09:26.358 --> 1:09:28.828
All right, oh...

1:09:28.861 --> 1:09:29.929
Geronimo!

1:09:35.067 --> 1:09:36.636
God dammit!

1:09:36.669 --> 1:09:37.670
I'm comin'.

1:09:59.558 --> 1:10:01.093
Whilst he...

1:10:01.127 --> 1:10:04.396
Who truly took it from them...

1:10:04.429 --> 1:10:06.632
I'm readin'!

1:10:06.666 --> 1:10:08.043
- You don't like me readin'?
- I'm listenin'.

1:10:08.067 --> 1:10:09.068
Huh?

1:10:12.437 --> 1:10:13.715
You look damn fine, little girl.

1:10:13.739 --> 1:10:14.573
Go on.

1:10:14.606 --> 1:10:16.441
Go on, back it up
in that chair now.

1:10:16.474 --> 1:10:17.810
Ooh!

1:10:17.844 --> 1:10:18.811
I'm gonna go get me
another drink.

1:10:18.845 --> 1:10:19.845
I'll be back.

1:10:23.983 --> 1:10:25.483
My man.

1:10:27.687 --> 1:10:28.654
Good night, right?

1:10:28.688 --> 1:10:29.789
Yeah. Say, Walter...

1:10:31.489 --> 1:10:32.424
Walter.

1:10:32.457 --> 1:10:35.094
I need your man
to send around a cruiser.

1:10:35.127 --> 1:10:36.028
What's going on?

1:10:36.062 --> 1:10:38.530
Uh, white trash
I've never seen before

1:10:38.563 --> 1:10:40.599
been ridin' by whoopin' it up.

1:10:41.499 --> 1:10:43.903
I feel like combustion
is on its way.

1:10:45.771 --> 1:10:47.439
- I'll talk to him.
- All right.

1:10:51.143 --> 1:10:52.778
Well, well, well.

1:10:52.812 --> 1:10:54.613
If it ain't
Mr. Rabble-rouser himself.

1:10:54.647 --> 1:10:55.580
How you doin', sir?

1:10:55.614 --> 1:10:58.918
Abel, set this man up
a drink here on me.

1:10:58.951 --> 1:11:01.586
Ah, I'll take a shot of Johnnie,

1:11:01.620 --> 1:11:05.523
and I'll buy it myself,
all right?

1:11:05.557 --> 1:11:08.728
- I don't need...
- Well, come on now, brother.

1:11:08.761 --> 1:11:10.595
Just trying to be hospitable.

1:11:10.630 --> 1:11:11.630
Oh.

1:11:12.632 --> 1:11:13.766
Trying to set me up, huh?

1:11:13.799 --> 1:11:15.201
- That's all you, baby.
- Hm.

1:11:15.234 --> 1:11:16.802
Come on, pretty boy.

1:11:16.836 --> 1:11:19.138
- Uh-uh.
- Dance with me.

1:11:19.171 --> 1:11:22.474
Show old Viola how you move.

1:11:22.507 --> 1:11:24.043
Careful with our V.

1:11:24.076 --> 1:11:25.610
She might bite.

1:11:25.645 --> 1:11:26.965
- Very good.
- Mind your business.

1:11:30.216 --> 1:11:32.517
Look what we have here.

1:11:32.550 --> 1:11:33.819
Let me get a water.

1:11:40.760 --> 1:11:42.228
Hello.

1:11:42.261 --> 1:11:43.229
Hey.

1:11:43.262 --> 1:11:44.230
How you doin'?

1:11:44.263 --> 1:11:45.698
Fine.

1:11:46.832 --> 1:11:47.943
Abel, give her a real drink.

1:11:47.967 --> 1:11:51.103
No. Water's fine.

1:11:51.137 --> 1:11:54.774
I suppose that you came
to dance with old Walter.

1:11:54.807 --> 1:11:56.608
Oh, we didn't lose.

1:11:56.642 --> 1:11:59.078
But you ain't won yet either.

1:11:59.111 --> 1:12:00.179
You scared?

1:13:40.312 --> 1:13:41.613
Ow!

1:13:43.749 --> 1:13:44.784
Whew!

1:13:46.919 --> 1:13:48.620
Hey, hotshot.

1:13:49.655 --> 1:13:51.290
Pour me one.

1:13:51.323 --> 1:13:56.662
And then you and me
do a little bump and grind.

1:13:58.964 --> 1:14:01.834
Vi, you need to calm down,
cool off.

1:14:01.867 --> 1:14:02.944
Come on, what you want,
a Coca-Cola?

1:14:02.968 --> 1:14:04.170
I'll buy it, I'll buy it. Hm?

1:14:04.203 --> 1:14:07.605
I don't want no Coca-Cola
and I don't wanna cool off.

1:14:09.375 --> 1:14:12.812
There are all these men
for you to dance with, so.

1:14:12.845 --> 1:14:14.222
Go on, get out,
you're embarrassing yourself,

1:14:14.246 --> 1:14:15.347
I'm with this lady.

1:14:15.381 --> 1:14:16.449
Go on.

1:14:16.482 --> 1:14:18.226
- Can I get another drink?
- What you want to drink?

1:14:18.250 --> 1:14:20.019
And you ain't gonna get
no water.

1:14:20.052 --> 1:14:21.619
Coca-Cola.

1:14:23.022 --> 1:14:24.622
You with this fresh meat?

1:14:24.657 --> 1:14:26.158
I'm with myself.

1:14:28.294 --> 1:14:30.096
Yourself, huh?

1:14:30.129 --> 1:14:31.263
Yeah.

1:14:33.332 --> 1:14:35.901
Well, you young and sassy now,

1:14:35.935 --> 1:14:39.839
but you gonna get old
