- Yes, you may.

1:29:51.917 --> 1:29:53.252
They do look good.

1:30:01.827 --> 1:30:03.662
- Ruth?
- Yes.

1:30:03.696 --> 1:30:04.930
Ruth, it's Grace Gordon.

1:30:04.964 --> 1:30:06.265
- Hi, Grace.
- Hi.

1:30:06.298 --> 1:30:07.633
Um...

1:30:10.069 --> 1:30:11.971
Boy, do I have
a lot to tell you.

1:30:12.004 --> 1:30:14.673
But you know that...
that bag of money you got?

1:30:14.707 --> 1:30:15.808
Mm-hm.

1:30:15.841 --> 1:30:18.010
Well, you ever think
of investin' it?

1:30:19.245 --> 1:30:22.348
As you said, play to our assets.

1:30:48.174 --> 1:30:51.811
In all the years you've been
scrapin' the sidewalks of DC,

1:30:51.844 --> 1:30:53.913
you two have never yet met?

1:30:53.946 --> 1:30:56.782
We travel down different paths.

1:30:56.816 --> 1:30:59.351
Mr. Celler travels with a union

1:30:59.385 --> 1:31:03.189
that doesn't think women
are to be treated as equal.

1:31:03.222 --> 1:31:05.324
And, as you know,
it's my lifelong ambition

1:31:05.357 --> 1:31:09.361
- to prove they should.
- Don't misrepresent me.

1:31:09.395 --> 1:31:13.165
I've said that women should
remain a protected class.

1:31:13.199 --> 1:31:15.768
Protected.
That's better than equal.

1:31:15.801 --> 1:31:17.736
Oh.

1:31:17.770 --> 1:31:19.105
- Miss Powell.
- Thank you.

1:31:19.138 --> 1:31:20.239
- Emanuel.
- Oh, thank you.

1:31:20.272 --> 1:31:22.308
This isn't gonna hurt much.

1:31:22.341 --> 1:31:23.819
We've got a bill
in Congress right now

1:31:23.843 --> 1:31:26.645
that wants to designate
bourbon whiskey

1:31:26.679 --> 1:31:28.948
as a distinctive product
of the United States.

1:31:28.981 --> 1:31:29.949
Think about that.

1:31:29.982 --> 1:31:31.884
Just a few short decades ago,

1:31:31.917 --> 1:31:34.120
this was illegal.

1:31:34.153 --> 1:31:37.923
Shows you how quick people
can have their minds changed.

1:31:37.957 --> 1:31:39.101
So what shall we drink to, huh?

1:31:39.125 --> 1:31:40.759
Well, let's get
right down to it.

1:31:40.793 --> 1:31:43.863
To fairer days
for the fairer sex,

1:31:43.896 --> 1:31:46.065
and to amending
the Civil Rights Bill

1:31:46.098 --> 1:31:48.100
to include women.

1:31:50.069 --> 1:31:52.071
Is that why you got her here,
the bill?

1:31:52.104 --> 1:31:55.074
Now, Emanuel, hear her out.

1:31:55.107 --> 1:31:56.308
You won't melt.

1:31:56.342 --> 1:31:58.878
Well, there will be
no undermining

1:31:58.911 --> 1:32:01.947
this long overdue issue.

1:32:01.981 --> 1:32:04.416
This bill is for the Negro man,
not women.

1:32:04.450 --> 1:32:06.352
- Not now.
- If not now, when?

1:32:06.385 --> 1:32:08.988
I believe Abigail Adams
asked that very question.

1:32:09.021 --> 1:32:11.991
188 years ago.

1:32:12.024 --> 1:32:13.135
Domestic violence and death,

1:32:13.159 --> 1:32:16.729
it just plays out across
our land night after night,

1:32:16.762 --> 1:32:18.864
and the police refuse
to even take the calls.

1:32:18.898 --> 1:32:21.433
They say she belongs to him.

1:32:21.467 --> 1:32:24.170
A woman doesn't have
any real protection

1:32:24.203 --> 1:32:28.807
unless she has equal access
to a job, to money, to freedom.

1:32:28.841 --> 1:32:31.143
And when they take off
to have their child,

1:32:31.177 --> 1:32:32.411
who will replace them?

1:32:32.444 --> 1:32:34.713
That is a problem.

1:32:34.747 --> 1:32:35.891
And when they return to work,

1:32:35.915 --> 1:32:37.716
who will rear their child?

1:32:37.750 --> 1:32:40.085
Women occupy one
of the most important roles

1:32:40.119 --> 1:32:44.089
in our society: Motherhood.

1:32:45.891 --> 1:32:48.394
It is a man's job
to protect the women.

1:32:48.427 --> 1:32:50.196
Now, Congressman Celler,

1:32:50.229 --> 1:32:53.832
let's not pretend that
all men protect their women,

1:32:53.866 --> 1:32:56.402
nor are we instructing them
to do so.

1:32:56.435 --> 1:32:58.804
And what you refer to

1:32:58.837 --> 1:33:03.976
as the most vital of all jobs
is unpaid,

1:33:04.009 --> 1:33:06.812
in a land
where the dollar is king.

1:33:08.280 --> 1:33:12.885
The mother is a pauper
or a slave.

1:33:15.888 --> 1:33:18.257
To be absolutely fair,

1:33:18.290 --> 1:33:22.528
probably women will do some
things I wish they wouldn't,

1:33:22.561 --> 1:33:24.363
but it's not our business
to tell them

1:33:24.396 --> 1:33:26.966
what they should do
with their freedom.

1:33:26.999 --> 1:33:29.368
But it is our business
to make sure

1:33:29.401 --> 1:33:31.770
that they have the right to try.

1:33:35.374 --> 1:33:36.842
Gentlemen.

1:33:39.878 --> 1:33:41.156
Don't even think about this,
Congressman,

1:33:41.180 --> 1:33:42.915
no piece of ass
worth throwin' ourselves

1:33:42.948 --> 1:33:44.025
under the load about to hit us.

1:33:44.049 --> 1:33:45.551
Watch your language.

1:33:45.584 --> 1:33:49.855
I said I was gonna do this,
so I will.

1:33:49.888 --> 1:33:52.191
Now, everything straight?

1:33:55.094 --> 1:33:56.438
Your face gonna
be in the dictionary

1:33:56.462 --> 1:33:57.997
under T for Traitor.

1:33:58.030 --> 1:33:59.398
Walter.

1:33:59.431 --> 1:34:01.533
There are no faces
of forgotten congressmen

1:34:01.567 --> 1:34:03.335
in the dictionary.

1:34:03.369 --> 1:34:05.504
It's all gonna be just fine.

1:34:05.537 --> 1:34:07.906
As long as everybody
follows the rules.

1:34:07.940 --> 1:34:11.443
What we have works.

1:34:24.223 --> 1:34:26.258
If you are determined

1:34:26.292 --> 1:34:29.261
to keep this bill as it stands,

1:34:29.295 --> 1:34:31.597
there will remain only one group

1:34:31.630 --> 1:34:34.433
of second-class citizens
in this country.

1:34:36.235 --> 1:34:41.006
Your mothers, sisters,
wives, and daughters.

1:34:42.508 --> 1:34:43.508
Women.

1:36:09.561 --> 1:36:11.563
So good of you to help.

1:36:11.597 --> 1:36:13.332
It's the least I could do.

1:36:13.365 --> 1:36:16.201
After what you did for me
and Angelina.

1:36:16.235 --> 1:36:18.003
Set us up in business.

1:36:18.036 --> 1:36:20.105
I'm Avon now.

1:36:20.139 --> 1:36:22.207
Door-to-door sales.

1:36:22.241 --> 1:36:24.410
And I've been meetin'
all sorts of interestin' people.

1:36:25.645 --> 1:36:27.680
Women sellin' to women.

1:36:27.714 --> 1:36:29.716
It's the future.

1:36:29.749 --> 1:36:31.083
Sure is my future.

1:36:33.552 --> 1:36:35.454
Well, you tell her,

1:36:35.487 --> 1:36:37.990
I'm not gonna charge her
interest.

1:36:38.023 --> 1:36:39.258
I want to help.

1:36:39.291 --> 1:36:40.926
That's awfully nice of you.

1:36:42.729 --> 1:36:44.596
- Come on, little one.
- Come on, baby girl.

1:36:45.732 --> 1:36:46.999
Go on in here.

1:36:48.333 --> 1:36:49.636
Wanna see a trick?

1:36:49.669 --> 1:36:51.470
All right.

1:36:51.503 --> 1:36:52.938
You see this?

1:36:55.642 --> 1:36:57.242
You see it, right?

1:36:58.377 --> 1:37:00.212
Blow on it.

1:37:00.245 --> 1:37:01.980
VoilÃ .

1:37:02.014 --> 1:37:03.182
Wait a minute.

1:37:04.416 --> 1:37:06.318
This is for you.

1:37:06.351 --> 1:37:08.620
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1:37:08.655 --> 1:37:10.657
I will be at the opening night.

1:37:10.690 --> 1:37:12.024
Make sure Dick brings his wife,

1:37:12.057 --> 1:37:13.525
do somethin' nice for a change.

1:37:15.561 --> 1:37:16.562
Ruth...

1:37:19.531 --> 1:37:23.636
Would you be interested
in calling it a date?

1:37:23.670 --> 1:37:24.771
A date?

1:37:26.038 --> 1:37:28.273
- With me?
- Come on.

1:37:31.076 --> 1:37:32.110
All right.

1:37:34.781 --> 1:37:37.082
All right.
Did she say all right?

1:37:37.115 --> 1:37:38.383
Yeah, she did.

1:37:38.417 --> 1:37:39.752
She said all right.

1:37:39.786 --> 1:37:40.786
All right.

1:37:43.055 --> 1:37:44.055
A date.

1:37:45.491 --> 1:37:46.659
You got a boyfriend.

1:37:46.693 --> 1:37:48.160
Oh, come on now.

1:37:49.461 --> 1:37:51.263
For women, huh?

1:37:51.296 --> 1:37:53.633
Negro men waited 300 years
to get a seat at the table

1:37:53.666 --> 1:37:55.067
and what you do?

1:37:55.100 --> 1:37:57.302
Pull out a chair for 'em.

1:37:57.336 --> 1:37:59.471
Walter, you're gonna grumble
about this

1:37:59.505 --> 1:38:01.440
for the rest of your life.

1:38:01.473 --> 1:38:03.108
- They're equal.
- Mm-hm.

1:38:03.141 --> 1:38:06.713
You're equal, we're all equal.

1:38:06.746 --> 1:38:10.148
It's what we do with it now
that matters.

1:38:10.182 --> 1:38:13.619
Never in history
have those in power

1:38:13.653 --> 1:38:16.789
handed over such an opportunity.

1:38:16.823 --> 1:38:18.557
See where this takes us.

1:38:20.559 --> 1:38:22.427
Wait, slow down, slow down,
there it is.

1:38:22.461 --> 1:38:23.595
Mm-hm.

1:38:23.629 --> 1:38:26.766
Any other bastard would have
kept her in a gilded cage.

1:38:28.300 --> 1:38:30.202
I gave her an exit.

1:38:33.773 --> 1:38:35.407
I did it for them.

1:38:39.111 --> 1:38:40.312
For her.

1:39:05.872 --> 1:39:07.874
- Best table in the house.
- Thank you.

1:39:20.887 --> 1:39:21.887
Well.

1:39:34.533 --> 1:39:36.168
- Thank you, Walter.
- Yes, sir.

1:39:36.201 --> 1:39:37.804
Well, well, well.

1:39:37.837 --> 1:39:40.707
Look at what
these women have done.

1:39:43.241 --> 1:39:44.309
Mattie.

1:39:44.343 --> 1:39:45.678
It smells like magic here.

1:39:45.712 --> 1:39:46.712
Doin' our best.

1:39:49.649 --> 1:39:51.416
Grace.

1:39:51.450 --> 1:39:53.619
You have managed to accomplish

1:39:53.653 --> 1:39:55.922
what 200 years
of Congress could not.

1:39:57.389 --> 1:40:00.492
Everyone seated at the table.

1:40:00.525 --> 1:40:03.261
And I guess you won't need
my services anymore.

1:40:03.295 --> 1:40:05.732
Hm, I'll need you,
perhaps not, but...

1:40:07.399 --> 1:40:08.467
want?

1:40:10.469 --> 1:40:13.271
Tonight under the tree.

1:40:13.305 --> 1:40:15.440
And you think we'll make it
past sunrise this time?

1:40:15.474 --> 1:40:16.943
Yes, ma'am.

1:40:16.976 --> 1:40:18.878
Hey, you,
quit hogging the biscuits!

1:40:18.911 --> 1:40:20.046
I'll take care of this.

1:40:20.079 --> 1:40:22.280
Just like you always have
to take what's not yours.

1:40:22.314 --> 1:40:24.249
Oh, I wouldn't miss it.

1:40:25.550 --> 1:40:27.486
Another time and place.

1:40:27.519 --> 1:40:29.554
So nice that we all get
to break bread together,

1:40:29.588 --> 1:40:31.423
- isn't it?
- Yes, sir.

1:40:31.456 --> 1:40:33.760
Especially
in such a charming place.

1:40:34.994 --> 1:40:36.528
And those biscuits
are the finest

1:40:36.561 --> 1:40:38.330
south of the Mason-Dixon line.

1:40:38.363 --> 1:40:40.365
And trust me,
there's none good north of it.

1:40:40.399 --> 1:40:43.201
I just want to smash it
in my face.

1:40:43.235 --> 1:40:44.336
- Mm.
- Isn't that good?

1:40:44.369 --> 1:40:46.271
And always a pleasure
to see you both.

1:40:46.304 --> 1:40:47.940
Enjoy your meal,
enjoy your dinner.

1:40:52.611 --> 1:40:54.446
My goodness.

1:40:54.479 --> 1:40:55.958
I've never seen a table
with such beautiful women

1:40:55.982 --> 1:40:56.883
in my life.

1:40:56.916 --> 1:40:58.985
Gentlemen,
you better behave yourselves.

1:41:05.323 --> 1:41:06.324
How y'all doin'?

1:41:06.358 --> 1:41:07.392
Good?

1:41:08.995 --> 1:41:10.629
Ah, my man.

1:41:13.298 --> 1:41:14.801
Have a drink.
